WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.760 --> 00:00:25.513
[magical tinkling]

2
00:00:33.880 --> 00:00:38.351
[man] We must begin our story. sad to say.
with an empty chair.

3
00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:42.790
If it were not empty.
we would not have a story.

4
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.630
But it is. and we do. and it is time to tell it.

5
00:00:54.840 --> 00:00:57.479
[birds twitter]

6
00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:07.033
[whooshing and tinkling]

7
00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:13.275
This is the story of my family.

8
00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:16.472
of my seven children. who are all very clever

9
00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:20.275
but all very. very. very naughty.

10
00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:25.156
Aaaaah! Aaaah! Aaaaa-aaaagh...!

11
00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:27.351
This is Nanny Whetstone.

12
00:01:27.560 --> 00:01:30.552
the 1 7th nanny I had hired
to look after my children.

13
00:01:30.760 --> 00:01:33.638
- Aaaaagh...!
- She was the strictest. the toughest

14
00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:37.310
and the most fearless nanny in all the land.

15
00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:42.033
As I went to work that day
at the funeral parlour.

16
00:01:42.240 --> 00:01:47.598
I was confident in the knowledge
that there was nothing. absolutely nothing

17
00:01:47.800 --> 00:01:51.634
- that my children could do to upset her.
- [shrieking approaches]

18
00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:53.796
They've eaten the baby!

19
00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:56.233
Except that.

20
00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:12.269
- [children] Quick! He's coming!
- Hide!

21
00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:14.391
- Quiet!
- Stop it!

22
00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:18.832
- Shh!
- [urgent whispering]

23
00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:21.553
[child burps]

24
00:02:31.200 --> 00:02:33.873
Children. where's Aggy?

25
00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:41.673
- [baby gurgles happily]
- [bells jingle]

26
00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:47.515
[rattle jingles]

27
00:02:49.040 --> 00:02:50.553
- Look at you.
- [Aggy gurgles]

28
00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:52.751
You're all cabbagey.

29
00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:56.396
Oh...and you're all gravy-y.

30
00:02:56.600 --> 00:03:01.116
As was your intention. Nanny Whetstone
has resigned from her post.

31
00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:04.995
I shall go to the agency this afternoon
and hire a new nanny.

32
00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:09.591
You will not drive her away
as you have done with her predecessors.

33
00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:11.916
[Aggy gurgles joyfully]

34
00:03:12.840 --> 00:03:13.795
Papa.

35
00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.995
Can't catch me out.
That showed 'em who's boss.

36
00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:19.998
Aaaagh! Whoa! Ooh! [grunts]

37
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.237
Three days. eight hours and 47 minutes.

38
00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:26.590
So that got rid of her...

39
00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:29.553
23 hours and 1 3 minutes
quicker than the last one.

40
00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:34.117
I think the turning point was definitely
eating the baby. Well done. Eric.

41
00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:37.879
Mr Brown. are you all right?

42
00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:39.877
I'm perfectly all right.

43
00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:45.200
Evangeline. could you let Cook know
that the new nanny has had to leave

44
00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:48.312
and I'm off to the agency to find a new one?

45
00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:58.472
Good. I'll just...

46
00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:10.590
[rattles doorknob]

47
00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:14.959
- Mrs Partridge?
- [woman] We're closed.

48
00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:17.390
- There's been a tiny hiccup.
- We're not here.

49
00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:19.830
- Please. let me in...
- Go away.

50
00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:23.350
Listen. they didn't eat the baby.
It was a chicken. actually.

51
00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:26.996
There's no more nannies! You've had your lot.
[slams door upstairs]

52
00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:34.040
[hinge creaks]

53
00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:39.708
[mysterious woman's voice]
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

54
00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:42.115
Is that you. Mrs Partridge?

55
00:04:43.080 --> 00:04:47.756
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

56
00:04:47.960 --> 00:04:51.509
I need her to start right away.
I'm late for a vital tea dance.

57
00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:54.314
Nanny McPhee is not on our books.

58
00:04:54.520 --> 00:04:58.229
Nanny McPhee is not on anyone's books.

59
00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:01.872
Nanny Whetstone's gone.

60
00:05:02.080 --> 00:05:06.039
There's a surprise. Hurry it up there. Spuds.

61
00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:11.030
Mr Brown's gone to the agency.
I said the children'll be fine with us.

62
00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:13.231
They won't be fine with me.

63
00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:16.591
I won't have them dirty blighters
in my kitchen. and that is that!

64
00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:20.349
I have it in writing. In writing!

65
00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:23.677
- [horrendous cacophony]
- [children shouting]

66
00:05:23.880 --> 00:05:27.156
- Well. that's the final straw.
- Pa!

67
00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:29.351
- There are no more nannies.
- Whoa!

68
00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:32.757
None. All over. finished.

69
00:05:32.960 --> 00:05:36.111
I've had to cancel my appointment
and that will cause trouble.

70
00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:41.110
- I told them not to. It wasn't my idea.
- Don't look at me! It's not my fault.

71
00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:44.039
Well. you seem intent on distressing me...

72
00:05:44.240 --> 00:05:47.357
Er...don't do that. darling. please.
That's my sore bit.

73
00:05:48.920 --> 00:05:51.957
You seem intent on distressing me.
so I'm going to distress you.

74
00:05:52.160 --> 00:05:55.914
You are to...to go to bed immediately.

75
00:05:56.120 --> 00:05:58.680
Before supper?

76
00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:03.196
Without supper.

77
00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:06.880
Did he say without supper?

78
00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:09.435
Never mind that.

79
00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:12.916
There's no more nannies.

80
00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:16.237
Poor him...and poor them.

81
00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:18.715
Poor them. my Aunt Fanny.

82
00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:21.593
They're the worstest. nastiest. horriblest...

83
00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:24.951
It'll be snow in August
before this family's straightened out.

84
00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:29.039
"Dear Nanny Whetstone.
I'm so very sorry."

85
00:06:29.240 --> 00:06:31.595
- "My children..."
- [children shout and fight]

86
00:06:31.800 --> 00:06:34.917
[girl] Eric. give it back to her!
Give it back now! Stop it!

87
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:36.599
My children.

88
00:06:39.080 --> 00:06:41.958
Eric! Eric. that's my teddy!

89
00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:45.277
- Eric. stop doing this!
- Give it back!

90
00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:50.232
- Stop fighting!
- Oi. you lot!

91
00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:53.193
- Quiet!
- [Sebastian hits notes on piano]

92
00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:57.837
You're driving your poor father
to distraction. Stop it.

93
00:06:58.880 --> 00:07:02.111
Lily. what's this word?

94
00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.676
Lovingly. "He took her lovingly by the hand."

95
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.393
What's your book about. Evangeline?

96
00:07:07.600 --> 00:07:11.673
It's about the daughter of a nice man
who remarries after his wife dies

97
00:07:11.880 --> 00:07:13.598
and the stepmother's horrid to her.

98
00:07:13.800 --> 00:07:16.109
Why doesn't the man stop her being horrid?

99
00:07:16.320 --> 00:07:20.871
Fathers all turn bad once their wives die.
They don't care any more.

100
00:07:21.080 --> 00:07:24.197
Simon. Yours does.

101
00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:26.072
No. he doesn't.

102
00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:31.035
Does he read to Chrissie
or play cricket with us like he used to?

103
00:07:31.240 --> 00:07:34.437
He doesn't even sing Loola-bye to Aggy.
We hardly see him.

104
00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:39.430
He loves you. Simon. You know that.
He's just had a lot on his mind since...

105
00:07:39.640 --> 00:07:41.949
Since Mother died.

106
00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:50.908
You used to be as close as anything.

107
00:07:51.120 --> 00:07:55.796
Not any more. All he cares about now
is getting himself a nice new wife.

108
00:07:58.160 --> 00:08:02.039
Well... I don't know if that's true or not.

109
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:04.549
but it might be nice to have a new mother.

110
00:08:04.760 --> 00:08:07.593
Don't you know anything about the world?

111
00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:11.156
Whoever he marries will be vile
and treat us like slaves.

112
00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:14.796
- You don't know that.
- Plenty of hard evidence for it.

113
00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:19.790
There isn't one stepmother in there
who's even halfway decent.

114
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.516
They're an evil breed. Anyway.
who ever likes other people's children?

115
00:08:24.720 --> 00:08:26.438
I like you.

116
00:08:26.640 --> 00:08:29.837
Yes. but you're a servant.
You're paid to like us.

117
00:08:30.040 --> 00:08:31.996
That doesn't count.

118
00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:38.351
- [guillotine clunks]
- I've got my work to be getting on with.

119
00:08:39.480 --> 00:08:41.391
[guillotine squeaks. then drops]

120
00:08:41.600 --> 00:08:43.556
I really am hungry. Evangeline.

121
00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:47.514
Could you maybe bring me
some secret toast and jam?

122
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:50.951
All right. forget the jam.
Just some secret toast.

123
00:08:54.040 --> 00:08:56.031
[match flares]

124
00:08:56.240 --> 00:08:58.390
[fire crackles]

125
00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:04.277
Shall I plump the cushion
on Mrs Brown's chair?

126
00:09:04.480 --> 00:09:06.994
I know you like to plump it yourself
sometimes.

127
00:09:07.200 --> 00:09:11.113
Oh. no. that's...that's all right.
You plump away. Evangeline. Thank you.

128
00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:21.513
I was wondering if I might make
Master Sebastian a piece of toast.

129
00:09:21.720 --> 00:09:24.837
Yes. I should think...
Er...no. under no circumstances. No.

130
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:26.837
I could do it secret-like.

131
00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:30.476
No. they'll hear him chewing
and then we're done for.

132
00:09:31.600 --> 00:09:33.079
No. they get nothing.

133
00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:35.032
Righto. Mr Brown.

134
00:09:37.880 --> 00:09:41.555
[mysterious woman's voice]
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

135
00:09:43.640 --> 00:09:45.358
Nanny McPhee.

136
00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:51.156
[sighs]

137
00:09:54.280 --> 00:09:56.157
No supper.

138
00:09:56.360 --> 00:09:59.432
Discipline. That's more like it.

139
00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:02.995
[whirring]

140
00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:04.713
[squeaks]

141
00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:10.079
[squeaking echoes]

142
00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:16.159
[mouse squeaks]

143
00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:18.952
[whimpers]

144
00:10:20.240 --> 00:10:21.593
[gasps]

145
00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:26.956
Now. you listen here. you pustular tykes.

146
00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:30.118
You ain't allowed in this kitchen.
not now. not ever.

147
00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:31.958
I have it in writing.

148
00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:37.159
Well. dear. the agency has closed its doors.

149
00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:40.511
What am I to do? Aunt Adelaide says...

150
00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:42.870
Your children are out of control. Cedric.

151
00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:47.915
And there was that thing she said
about their needing a female influence. I...

152
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:51.599
You know what she's like.
She'll stop the allowance

153
00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:56.590
unless I marry again and give them
a new mother within the month.

154
00:10:56.800 --> 00:11:01.874
A month. I mean. it's unbearable.
But l... I had to... I had to promise.

155
00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:09.195
Remember we talked about
what would happen without her money.

156
00:11:09.400 --> 00:11:11.630
The bank will take the house.

157
00:11:11.840 --> 00:11:15.913
There'll be debtors' prison for me.
workhouse for the older children.

158
00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:19.192
Goodness only knows
what'll happen to little Chrissie.

159
00:11:19.400 --> 00:11:21.436
And as for Aggy...

160
00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:23.870
it's unimaginable.

161
00:11:24.080 --> 00:11:25.832
[squeaking]

162
00:11:27.440 --> 00:11:29.510
[springs boing]

163
00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:35.039
Where are you? You mewling half-bakes!

164
00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:37.674
I'm ready for you. And I'm hard!

165
00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:39.757
[boing!]

166
00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.872
[children's laughter and shouting echoes]

167
00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.076
This is fun!

168
00:11:48.160 --> 00:11:49.479
We got Cook!

169
00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:53.958
[mysterious woman's voice]
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

170
00:11:54.160 --> 00:11:56.913
- [Chrissie] Ju-ump!
- [Cook shrieks through gag]

171
00:11:57.120 --> 00:11:59.793
Eric. you're not making another bomb.
are you?

172
00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:02.070
[he cackles maniacally]

173
00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:05.397
[echoing] McPhee...

174
00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:07.716
- Whee!
- Jump!

175
00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:10.195
- Oh!
- Jump!

176
00:12:10.400 --> 00:12:12.197
[yells]

177
00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:17.554
- They're in the kitchen.
- No! No! You took them down for toast!

178
00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:20.479
I never did!
You sent them to bed with no dinner.

179
00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:22.033
- That's what done it!
- Don't tell...

180
00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:25.152
- [banging]
- [thunderclap]

181
00:12:25.360 --> 00:12:27.510
[electrical crackle]

182
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:32.879
- I'll. er...
- Why don't you...?

183
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:34.672
- I'll go.
- No. I'd better...

184
00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:37.599
- Well. no. I can...
- You. erm... I'll...

185
00:12:37.800 --> 00:12:41.475
- I'll be off. then.
- Yes. you... I'll just...

186
00:12:41.680 --> 00:12:43.238
[electrical crackle]

187
00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:46.910
[thunder rumbles]

188
00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:03.237
[door creaks]

189
00:13:05.320 --> 00:13:08.710
[thunderclap]

190
00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:14.234
Good evening. Mr Brown.
I am Nanny McPhee.

191
00:13:15.680 --> 00:13:18.797
Oh. you're... Er...of course.

192
00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:21.195
Good heavens. I suppose the agency...

193
00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:25.598
I do not belong to any agency. Mr Brown.
I am a government nanny.

194
00:13:25.800 --> 00:13:28.519
A government nanny? How...

195
00:13:29.960 --> 00:13:31.109
.. unusual.

196
00:13:31.320 --> 00:13:32.878
May I come in?

197
00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:36.311
Yes. by all means. do...do come in.

198
00:13:36.520 --> 00:13:40.354
- Hm.
- [thunder rumbles]

199
00:13:40.560 --> 00:13:44.553
I understand you have
extremely ill-behaved children.

200
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:48.435
No. No. no. No.
No... Good grief. what a suggestion.

201
00:13:48.640 --> 00:13:50.756
[china shatters. child roars]

202
00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:52.916
- Playful.
- [child] Shut up!

203
00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:54.997
What are your main concerns?

204
00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:56.315
Concerns?

205
00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:59.239
Mm. Do they go to bed when they're told?

206
00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:01.795
Well. no. not. er... No.

207
00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:05.879
- Do they get up when they're told?
- Er...well. no. not exactly.

208
00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:09.550
- Get dressed when they're told?
- Now. that's a good question.

209
00:14:09.760 --> 00:14:14.436
- Do they say "please" and "thank you"?
- In what context?

210
00:14:14.640 --> 00:14:17.996
- That will do to be going on with.
- [child laughs wickedly]

211
00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:21.909
- Your children need me.
- [china shatters]

212
00:14:22.120 --> 00:14:25.795
I'll go and make sure everything's
in order before I introduce you.

213
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:28.719
I shall introduce myself.

214
00:14:28.920 --> 00:14:32.196
Please. Mr Brown.
go back to your newspaper.

215
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:38.635
- [tiny bells tinkling]
- [clattering and wild yelling]

216
00:14:43.240 --> 00:14:46.755
[children squeal and yell]

217
00:14:49.280 --> 00:14:52.750
[muffled shouting]

218
00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:54.473
Oh. look.

219
00:14:56.560 --> 00:14:59.154
The door's open and there's nobody there.

220
00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:02.193
[muffled shrieks]

221
00:15:02.400 --> 00:15:04.311
I am here.

222
00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:06.829
I am Nanny McPhee.

223
00:15:07.040 --> 00:15:09.600
Oh. did...did somebody speak?

224
00:15:09.800 --> 00:15:13.713
- I didn't hear anything.
- That's because nobody's there.

225
00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:16.513
- [gasps]
- [clanging]

226
00:15:16.720 --> 00:15:20.030
Then listen carefully and try to hear this.

227
00:15:20.240 --> 00:15:23.391
Stop what you are doing.
put the kitchen to rights

228
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:25.318
and go upstairs to bed.

229
00:15:25.520 --> 00:15:28.796
[muffled shouts]

230
00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:32.629
- Did you hear what I said?
- I've just had an idea.

231
00:15:32.840 --> 00:15:37.072
Why don't we play here
in the kitchen all night long?

232
00:15:37.280 --> 00:15:39.430
Let's. let's!

233
00:15:41.880 --> 00:15:45.555
- Excellent notion.
- [Sebastian] Tomatoes!

234
00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:49.275
Jump! Jump. jump! Jump!

235
00:15:49.480 --> 00:15:53.109
- [magical wind rushes]
- [Chrissie] Jump. jump. jump. jump!

236
00:15:53.320 --> 00:15:56.073
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump!

237
00:15:56.280 --> 00:15:58.510
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump!

238
00:15:58.720 --> 00:16:01.553
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump...jump...

239
00:16:01.760 --> 00:16:04.399
- jump.
- [whines]

240
00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:12.520
- [creaking]
- [magical wind rushes]

241
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:22.998
Government nanny?

242
00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:25.919
[crashing thud]

243
00:16:26.120 --> 00:16:27.314
[Chrissie] What's she done?

244
00:16:27.520 --> 00:16:31.433
- [Eric] She's done something to us!
- They went in the pot!

245
00:16:31.640 --> 00:16:33.073
[Chrissie] I can't stop!

246
00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:34.793
[Eric] She banged her stick!

247
00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:36.911
[Chrissie] I'm going to be sick!

248
00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.998
[yells and squeals]

249
00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:44.836
- [Eric] It must be magic!
- [Lily] What's happening?

250
00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:51.514
- [Lily] Please. Simon. let's stop!
- We've got to stop!

251
00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:54.188
- Let's stop!
- Let's stop!

252
00:16:57.560 --> 00:17:00.154
- Well. stop if you want. then!
- We can't!

253
00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:01.554
It's her fault!

254
00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:03.557
It started when she banged the stick!

255
00:17:03.760 --> 00:17:07.196
- [Chrissie] I can't stop!
- [Eric] Slow down!

256
00:17:07.840 --> 00:17:09.159
Simon!

257
00:17:09.360 --> 00:17:12.716
Come on. whoever you are!
Let's stop this and go to bed!

258
00:17:14.560 --> 00:17:17.279
- Say "please".
- I never say "please".

259
00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:18.515
Very well.

260
00:17:18.720 --> 00:17:20.995
- Please!
- Please!

261
00:17:21.200 --> 00:17:23.873
- Don't touch Aggy!
- Wait!

262
00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:25.718
Say it!

263
00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:28.992
Actually. Simon. would you.
because this baby's gonna blow!

264
00:17:29.200 --> 00:17:33.034
- And Aggy's gonna go in the stockpot!
- Put her back. Chrissie!

265
00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:36.589
Oh. for goodness' sake! Please. then!

266
00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:42.032
[Chrissie] Take Aggy off me!

267
00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:45.038
Please. Nanny McPhee.

268
00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:48.313
[Tora] Chrissie. don't!

269
00:17:49.480 --> 00:17:52.677
- Say it!
- [Eric] Take Aggy out!

270
00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:55.474
- [Tora] No. Lily!
- Say it!

271
00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:57.318
Simon!

272
00:17:57.520 --> 00:18:01.149
- [Lily] I can't stop myself!
- [pots clatter musically]

273
00:18:01.360 --> 00:18:03.669
Please. Nanny McPhee.

274
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:06.835
[Lily] I'm going to jump!

275
00:18:07.040 --> 00:18:08.359
Too late!

276
00:18:16.400 --> 00:18:18.595
[magical wind rushes]

277
00:18:20.880 --> 00:18:22.154
[tiny bell rings]

278
00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:24.430
Blimey.

279
00:18:24.640 --> 00:18:26.676
Up to bed. please.

280
00:18:39.080 --> 00:18:42.197
Goodnight. Mrs Blatherwick.
Goodnight. Evangeline.

281
00:18:42.400 --> 00:18:44.675
[servants] Goodnight. Nanny McPhee.

282
00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:49.793
When Mr Brown said no dinner.
I thought they'd be down in a trice.

283
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:51.592
They've been ever so quiet.

284
00:18:51.800 --> 00:18:55.554
Don't you fret.
They don't dare come in this kitchen.

285
00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:58.274
I have it in writing.

286
00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:01.119
[sighs contentedly]

287
00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:03.952
- Be careful. Aggy.
- [jingling]

288
00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:08.870
It's Mama's rattle.
and it's the only thing we've got of hers.

289
00:19:09.080 --> 00:19:11.355
[Aggy gurgles]

290
00:19:11.560 --> 00:19:14.552
- What on earth are you doing?
- Getting ready for bed.

291
00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:18.639
- What she told us to do.
- Since when did we do what we're told?

292
00:19:18.840 --> 00:19:21.559
Since we nearly got Cook blown up
and Aggy boiled.

293
00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:28.110
May I just remind you of something?
We got rid of the last 1 7 nannies.

294
00:19:28.320 --> 00:19:30.436
We're getting rid of this one too.

295
00:19:30.640 --> 00:19:32.756
[children all shout]

296
00:19:32.960 --> 00:19:35.190
Fine! Be brave. then!

297
00:19:35.400 --> 00:19:40.235
Yes. well. I nearly got blown up!
And anyway. l...

298
00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:46.236
[magical tinkling]

299
00:19:46.440 --> 00:19:47.793
Hm.

300
00:20:04.400 --> 00:20:08.234
You must feel at such a disadvantage.
Nanny McPhee.

301
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:09.589
In what way?

302
00:20:09.800 --> 00:20:12.598
We know your name
but you don't know ours.

303
00:20:12.800 --> 00:20:15.155
[other children giggle]

304
00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:18.158
Pleased to meet you.
I'm Oglington Fartworthy.

305
00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:22.638
- [farty noise]
- [giggling]

306
00:20:26.360 --> 00:20:29.272
How do you do?

307
00:20:31.040 --> 00:20:33.315
That's F-A-R-T.

308
00:20:33.520 --> 00:20:37.115
- Fartworthy.
- [giggling swells]

309
00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:41.514
Booger McHorsefanny.

310
00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:43.870
Knickers O'Muffin.

311
00:20:44.080 --> 00:20:45.274
Sandra.

312
00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:46.515
Bum.

313
00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.836
I'm Bum!

314
00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:50.758
Oh. Bosoms.

315
00:20:50.960 --> 00:20:53.235
[children giggle]

316
00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:55.355
Bum.

317
00:20:55.560 --> 00:20:59.758
You can't be Bum. Aggy.
Sebastian's Bum. You're Poop.

318
00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:01.234
Poop Bum.

319
00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:03.476
You can't be Poop and Bum.

320
00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:07.195
- [children laughing]
- [Aggy giggles then stops]

321
00:21:23.280 --> 00:21:25.350
[whispers] Goodnight. Agatha.

322
00:21:32.480 --> 00:21:34.869
Goodnight. Sebastian.

323
00:21:35.080 --> 00:21:37.071
Goodnight. Tora.

324
00:21:37.280 --> 00:21:39.271
Goodnight. Christianna.

325
00:21:40.760 --> 00:21:42.671
Goodnight. Lily.

326
00:21:42.880 --> 00:21:44.711
Goodnight. Eric.

327
00:21:48.040 --> 00:21:50.076
Goodnight. Simon.

328
00:21:55.560 --> 00:21:59.838
There is something you should understand
about the way I work.

329
00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:04.272
When you need me but do not want me.
then I must stay.

330
00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:10.396
When you want me but no longer need me.
then I have to go.

331
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:17.433
It's rather sad. really. but there it is.

332
00:22:18.520 --> 00:22:21.318
We will never want you.

333
00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:24.870
Then I will never go.

334
00:22:29.680 --> 00:22:32.478
- Goodnight. children.
- [magical tinkling]

335
00:22:35.640 --> 00:22:39.030
How did she know our names?
No one ever knows our names.

336
00:22:39.240 --> 00:22:40.992
- Magic.
- Witchcraft.

337
00:22:41.200 --> 00:22:44.909
It doesn't matter.
We're getting rid of her tomorrow.

338
00:22:45.960 --> 00:22:49.077
- [owl hoots]
- [mutters]

339
00:22:53.480 --> 00:22:58.190
- [tinkling wind rushes]
- What? Wha... What? What?

340
00:22:58.400 --> 00:23:00.311
I did knock.

341
00:23:00.520 --> 00:23:04.149
Of course. You weren't just
creeping up on me. What a suggestion.

342
00:23:04.360 --> 00:23:08.239
- The children are all in bed and asleep.
- Good. Really?

343
00:23:08.440 --> 00:23:10.112
Hm.

344
00:23:11.280 --> 00:23:14.556
- Good grief.
- I shall see myself to my room.

345
00:23:14.760 --> 00:23:16.557
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

346
00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:23.197
No. wait.

347
00:23:24.400 --> 00:23:27.358
What do you... I mean. how...
What are your terms?

348
00:23:28.960 --> 00:23:31.997
Your children require five lessons.

349
00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:36.159
Lesson one. to go to bed
when they're told. is complete.

350
00:23:36.360 --> 00:23:40.512
As for my terms.
I take Sunday afternoons off.

351
00:23:41.560 --> 00:23:43.835
Goodnight.

352
00:23:45.680 --> 00:23:46.954
Interesting.

353
00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:50.277
[magical breeze sighs]

354
00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:54.799
- [birds twitter]
- [geese honk]

355
00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:57.036
[buzzing]

356
00:23:58.480 --> 00:24:01.392
[grunts and snuffles]

357
00:24:01.600 --> 00:24:03.397
Time to get up.

358
00:24:04.520 --> 00:24:06.590
[grunts] No.

359
00:24:09.320 --> 00:24:12.676
Hm. I shall give you half an hour to be up.

360
00:24:12.880 --> 00:24:16.270
washed. dressed. teeth cleaned. beds made

361
00:24:16.480 --> 00:24:20.075
and out into the garden
for healthful fresh air before breakfast.

362
00:24:20.280 --> 00:24:24.796
Lessons start at nine...sharp.

363
00:24:25.000 --> 00:24:26.877
[magical breeze sighs]

364
00:24:27.080 --> 00:24:31.232
I don't know about you lot.
but I want to stay in bed.

365
00:24:31.440 --> 00:24:34.955
Sebastian. run the thermometer
under the hot tap.

366
00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:38.675
Chrissie. chalk. Eric. crayons. Lily. pepper.

367
00:24:38.880 --> 00:24:41.838
How do you know
she won't do something horrid to us?

368
00:24:42.040 --> 00:24:43.473
I worked it out.

369
00:24:43.680 --> 00:24:47.798
She's a trained hypnotist.
That's how she made us do those things.

370
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:50.798
Don't look directly at her
and she can't hypnotise us.

371
00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:52.228
[knock at door]

372
00:24:52.440 --> 00:24:53.634
- Morning. Mr Brown.
- Morning.

373
00:24:53.840 --> 00:24:56.513
I'm off to work early.
We're busy at the mortuary.

374
00:24:56.720 --> 00:25:01.919
Some bout of influenza at Archway
is carrying off all the old folks... Ah-ah-ah!

375
00:25:02.120 --> 00:25:05.317
Still. what's bad for them
is good for us. [chuckles]

376
00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:07.272
Poor things.

377
00:25:07.480 --> 00:25:10.040
Well. I know. That. too. Of course.

378
00:25:13.080 --> 00:25:16.470
- [door slams]
- Odd. She normally says. "Have a nice day."

379
00:25:16.680 --> 00:25:19.672
or "Don't forget your jacket" if it's cold out.

380
00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:22.838
Very odd. Most peculiar.

381
00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:24.632
[magical wind rushes]

382
00:25:24.840 --> 00:25:27.195
Hm.

383
00:25:28.240 --> 00:25:31.710
- I did knock.
- Did you? I didn't hear.

384
00:25:31.920 --> 00:25:33.478
I was talking to...

385
00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:37.797
Never mind.

386
00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:40.833
I believe the children
will be staying in bed today.

387
00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:43.759
The children? What. all day?
Are they ill? What's wrong?

388
00:25:43.960 --> 00:25:47.316
Nothing. I know precisely what to do.
Please leave it to me.

389
00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:49.750
You managed them splendidly last night.

390
00:25:49.960 --> 00:25:51.632
If they are under the weather.

391
00:25:51.840 --> 00:25:54.912
give them what they want.
ice-cream and jelly and suchlike.

392
00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:58.192
My late wife was very particular.
If ever they were ill.

393
00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:02.757
she used to wait on them hand and foot...
even if they weren't ill at all.

394
00:26:02.960 --> 00:26:07.158
I shall be sure to give them
exactly what they need.

395
00:26:07.360 --> 00:26:11.751
Excellent. Excellent.
Well. I'll just be off to work. then.

396
00:26:20.080 --> 00:26:22.640
[magical tinkling]

397
00:26:22.840 --> 00:26:24.478
She's coming!

398
00:26:24.680 --> 00:26:27.558
Remember. everyone. don't look in her eyes.

399
00:26:31.880 --> 00:26:33.154
Dear me.

400
00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:37.353
[coughs] We can't get up. We're ill.

401
00:26:37.560 --> 00:26:39.630
Colds in our doses.

402
00:26:39.840 --> 00:26:41.319
And kemperakurk.

403
00:26:41.520 --> 00:26:44.034
We think it bight be the beasles.

404
00:26:44.240 --> 00:26:45.719
Got measig.

405
00:26:45.920 --> 00:26:48.434
Good heavens.

406
00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:51.712
Then there is of course
no question of your getting up.

407
00:26:51.920 --> 00:26:57.233
I'm very sorry to have to tell you all
that you'll have to stay in bed.

408
00:27:01.080 --> 00:27:02.195
Hm.

409
00:27:02.400 --> 00:27:04.356
- [magical wind rushes]
- [creaking]

410
00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:08.269
[crashing thud]

411
00:27:11.840 --> 00:27:14.832
[children giggle]

412
00:27:16.400 --> 00:27:18.834
[giggling dies away]

413
00:27:20.600 --> 00:27:23.512
- Ah.
- I don't feel well.

414
00:27:23.720 --> 00:27:28.191
- I think I've got a temperature.
- Don't be daft.

415
00:27:30.640 --> 00:27:32.437
Simon. I can't get up.

416
00:27:32.640 --> 00:27:35.598
- You must have looked at her. then.
- I did not look.

417
00:27:35.800 --> 00:27:40.271
I was under the covers the whole time.
Simon. I can't get up either.

418
00:27:40.480 --> 00:27:43.278
- [Sebastian] I can't get up!
- [Eric] I'm stuck like glue!

419
00:27:43.480 --> 00:27:45.038
[Chrissie] I'm stuck. too!

420
00:27:46.880 --> 00:27:50.793
Hypnosis. eh? Bang goes that theory.

421
00:27:54.880 --> 00:27:56.552
Good morning.

422
00:28:04.720 --> 00:28:07.280
[both] Morning. Mr B!

423
00:28:07.480 --> 00:28:09.869
- [they laugh uproariously]
- Good morning. Mr Jowls. Mr Wheen.

424
00:28:10.080 --> 00:28:13.629
- [both] Thought we'd get you that time.
- No. not this time.

425
00:28:13.840 --> 00:28:18.072
- Nice tea dance. Mr B?
- Ooh. lovely. I shouldn't wonder.

426
00:28:18.280 --> 00:28:21.477
No. I didn't even get there. Disaster.
Children. you know.

427
00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:24.194
- We do know.
- We've said it before.

428
00:28:24.400 --> 00:28:27.631
It's not funerals
you should be in the business of.

429
00:28:27.840 --> 00:28:30.070
[both] It's christenings.

430
00:28:30.280 --> 00:28:32.953
[they laugh uproariously]

431
00:28:38.360 --> 00:28:42.399
Good morning.
Just excuse me a moment. would you?

432
00:28:42.600 --> 00:28:44.830
[woman] Cedric.
let me not beat about the bush.

433
00:28:45.040 --> 00:28:46.632
Your children are out of control.

434
00:28:46.840 --> 00:28:50.196
You need a wife
and your children need a mother.

435
00:28:50.400 --> 00:28:55.793
If you do not remarry by the end of the month.
steps will have to be taken.

436
00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:58.878
Oh. dear. Oh. dear. oh. dear. oh. dear.

437
00:29:00.680 --> 00:29:03.353
What's your wife like?

438
00:29:03.560 --> 00:29:07.951
Never mind. Less than a month to go.
There's nothing for it.

439
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:12.119
It'll have to be that woman...
the dreadful one.

440
00:29:13.280 --> 00:29:17.478
Mr Jowls. do you recollect
that...enthusiastic lady?

441
00:29:17.680 --> 00:29:22.117
Mrs Swiftly. was it? Or was it
Mrs Thadius something last year?

442
00:29:22.320 --> 00:29:25.153
- Mrs Thadius Quickly?
- Oh. don't.

443
00:29:25.360 --> 00:29:30.036
"Oh. Mr Brown. you are a saint. You have
a lovely look of kindness about you."

444
00:29:30.240 --> 00:29:35.598
What I wouldn't give for a man like you.
Mr Brown. in my hour of need.

445
00:29:37.040 --> 00:29:38.917
- That one?
- Yes. that one.

446
00:29:39.120 --> 00:29:41.554
We buried Mr Quickly last autumn.
Poor devil.

447
00:29:41.760 --> 00:29:45.275
- He was happy to go.
- He was her third.

448
00:29:45.480 --> 00:29:49.109
You don't happen to know
if... if she ever...ever. erm...

449
00:29:49.320 --> 00:29:51.709
remarried? You know. number four?

450
00:29:51.920 --> 00:29:55.913
Mr Brown. you're not thinking what I think
you're thinking. are you. Mr Brown?

451
00:29:57.280 --> 00:29:59.748
Good grief. no! No. no. No. No.

452
00:29:59.960 --> 00:30:03.873
No. No. no... no. What a thought. No. No.

453
00:30:04.080 --> 00:30:06.355
[both] Ohhh...

454
00:30:06.560 --> 00:30:08.835
- [gloopy bubbling]
- [children] What's that?

455
00:30:09.040 --> 00:30:12.396
Measle medicine.
to be administered once an hour.

456
00:30:12.600 --> 00:30:14.989
Actually. I'm not sure it is measles.

457
00:30:15.200 --> 00:30:18.078
How can it be anything other?

458
00:30:18.280 --> 00:30:20.874
The chalky-white faces. the livid spots.

459
00:30:21.080 --> 00:30:24.436
- the temperatures of 1 20 degrees.
- [sizzle]

460
00:30:24.640 --> 00:30:27.712
I've seen it time and again. Measles.

461
00:30:29.120 --> 00:30:31.111
Definitely.

462
00:30:31.320 --> 00:30:34.437
[thick. gloopy gurgling]

463
00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:38.155
Urgh!

464
00:30:38.360 --> 00:30:42.638
- Open.
- [Lily] Simon. don't!

465
00:30:42.840 --> 00:30:45.070
- [sludgy bubbling]
- I'm not taking that.

466
00:30:45.280 --> 00:30:47.794
Then you will not get any better.

467
00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:49.672
Believe me.

468
00:30:49.880 --> 00:30:52.189
[Chrissie] It's moving!

469
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:55.869
Open wide.

470
00:30:57.920 --> 00:30:59.512
Wider.

471
00:30:59.720 --> 00:31:03.838
[Simon grunts and gags]

472
00:31:04.040 --> 00:31:05.155
Urgh!

473
00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:11.433
- [thick. gloopy gulping]
- Urgh!

474
00:31:12.920 --> 00:31:15.229
[retches]

475
00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:17.670
[Eric] Simon. spit it out!

476
00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:22.192
You'll have to swallow it sooner or later.
so I suggest you get it over with.

477
00:31:23.120 --> 00:31:25.998
- [thick. bubbling gulp]
- [gags]

478
00:31:28.080 --> 00:31:31.436
Very good. Who's next?

479
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:33.879
"Took..."

480
00:31:34.080 --> 00:31:35.672
"He..."

481
00:31:35.880 --> 00:31:38.678
"He took her lovingly..."

482
00:31:38.880 --> 00:31:43.556
"He took her lovingly by the...the hand."

483
00:31:43.760 --> 00:31:48.390
- [magical breeze sighs]
- Oh! Nanny McPhee. you startled me.

484
00:31:48.600 --> 00:31:49.999
It was that quiet.

485
00:31:50.200 --> 00:31:54.398
I just got to practising my sounds.
Lily's teaching me to read.

486
00:31:54.600 --> 00:31:55.874
That is good.

487
00:31:56.080 --> 00:32:00.119
They're all good... underneath it all.

488
00:32:01.400 --> 00:32:05.712
- A favourite of yours?
- Don't know.

489
00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:07.911
I haven't finished it yet.

490
00:32:08.120 --> 00:32:12.159
- The stepmother's a bit of a horror. though.
- Oh. indeed.

491
00:32:12.360 --> 00:32:14.794
It's a pity stories aren't about real people.

492
00:32:15.000 --> 00:32:18.834
This one seems a farm girl.
but I'll bet a pound to a penny

493
00:32:19.040 --> 00:32:22.715
he finds out she's really an educated lady.

494
00:32:22.920 --> 00:32:25.150
And then he falls for her.

495
00:32:25.360 --> 00:32:27.396
You must read it and find out.

496
00:32:27.600 --> 00:32:30.398
He wouldn't love her if she couldn't read.

497
00:32:30.600 --> 00:32:33.672
He'd think her stupid

498
00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:37.793
and worthless and beneath him.

499
00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:39.069
Hm.

500
00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:48.277
[tinkling breeze sighs]

501
00:32:53.760 --> 00:32:57.992
Buttered spuds for lunch
with boiled beef. apple pie and custard.

502
00:32:58.200 --> 00:33:00.395
Hm.

503
00:33:01.960 --> 00:33:06.078
I think the children will be requiring
something a little more...

504
00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:08.111
austere today.

505
00:33:08.320 --> 00:33:09.958
'Orse what?

506
00:33:10.160 --> 00:33:13.914
The children are not quite themselves.
Mrs Blatherwick.

507
00:33:14.120 --> 00:33:18.398
God! That means jellies and ice-cream.
raspberry cordial and God knows what else.

508
00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:21.068
Well. I'd better get cracking. then.

509
00:33:21.280 --> 00:33:23.350
Evangeline!

510
00:33:23.560 --> 00:33:25.710
Where is that lump?

511
00:33:25.920 --> 00:33:29.310
It'll be snow in August
before that one's there when you need her.

512
00:33:29.520 --> 00:33:34.196
Calm yourself. Mrs Blatherwick.
I'm in charge today.

513
00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:38.598
I understand that you were once
in the armed forces.

514
00:33:41.000 --> 00:33:44.959
I was that. Cooked at a training camp
in Gloucestershire.

515
00:33:45.160 --> 00:33:47.230
Kept those boys strong. I did.

516
00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:52.833
I'm sure you did. Perhaps a broth
of some sort for the children.

517
00:33:53.040 --> 00:33:55.076
You must be an expert.

518
00:33:55.280 --> 00:33:58.033
Best thin potato gruel with peelings in?

519
00:33:58.240 --> 00:34:00.708
That always got 'em groaning
but kept 'em strong.

520
00:34:00.920 --> 00:34:02.956
Are you well supplied with peelings?

521
00:34:08.200 --> 00:34:10.236
These'll do. Only a day old.

522
00:34:10.440 --> 00:34:13.000
[tinkling breeze blows]

523
00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:19.630
A bit of gristle for flavour. Ever so tasty.

524
00:34:19.840 --> 00:34:21.432
[chuckles]

525
00:34:21.640 --> 00:34:26.350
Get that down you.
There's a lot of goodness in a turkey neck.

526
00:34:26.560 --> 00:34:28.630
That'll put the hairs back on your chest.

527
00:34:28.840 --> 00:34:34.949
[inhales deeply] Smell that.
That is the smell that forged this empire.

528
00:34:35.160 --> 00:34:39.278
That pong is the pong of conquerors.

529
00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:42.517
All right. men. As you were.

530
00:34:44.200 --> 00:34:46.919
They actually are starving us.

531
00:34:47.120 --> 00:34:50.271
I wonder how long it will take for us all to die.

532
00:34:52.960 --> 00:34:54.916
[cat yowls]

533
00:34:58.520 --> 00:35:00.988
[floorboards creak]

534
00:35:05.760 --> 00:35:08.513
Quickly...

535
00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:11.996
Quickly. Quickly. Quickly...

536
00:35:12.200 --> 00:35:14.668
Mrs Selma Quickly.

537
00:35:15.800 --> 00:35:17.950
[footsteps approach]

538
00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:23.472
Have you lazy lot been in bed all day?

539
00:35:23.680 --> 00:35:25.432
Evangeline.

540
00:35:25.640 --> 00:35:27.756
You've been doing measles. haven't you?

541
00:35:27.960 --> 00:35:30.155
The situation's very simple. Evangeline.

542
00:35:30.360 --> 00:35:33.432
The nanny. who in my opinion is a witch.

543
00:35:33.640 --> 00:35:36.279
made us ill and fed us boiled-down toads.

544
00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:40.234
Nanny McPhee is not a witch. Eric.
You're very naughty to say so.

545
00:35:40.440 --> 00:35:42.590
I'm sure she knew what she was doing.

546
00:35:42.800 --> 00:35:46.395
- She must be fully trained.
- Yes. but as what?

547
00:35:46.600 --> 00:35:49.068
I'm unbelievably hungry. Evangeline.

548
00:35:49.280 --> 00:35:53.637
Can you please get us
something decent to eat?

549
00:35:53.840 --> 00:35:56.070
Did you just say "please"?

550
00:35:56.280 --> 00:35:58.350
[children] Please. please. Evangeline!

551
00:36:00.080 --> 00:36:03.436
Well. children.
I hear you've been in bed all day

552
00:36:03.640 --> 00:36:05.198
but that you're better now.

553
00:36:05.400 --> 00:36:07.550
It wasn't our fault.

554
00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:11.548
I'm sure it wasn't anybody's fault.
You can't help it if you're ill.

555
00:36:11.760 --> 00:36:13.512
But you're better now.

556
00:36:13.720 --> 00:36:15.756
- [creaking]
- [whooshing]

557
00:36:15.960 --> 00:36:19.316
[crashing thud]

558
00:36:25.760 --> 00:36:27.113
- Papa?
- Yes. Chrissie?

559
00:36:27.320 --> 00:36:30.357
Now that we're better. can we get up?

560
00:36:30.560 --> 00:36:33.438
- Erm...
- [children] Can we get up. please?

561
00:36:35.520 --> 00:36:37.954
[tinkling breeze blows]

562
00:36:42.640 --> 00:36:44.756
Of course you can.

563
00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:46.552
Read to us.

564
00:36:46.760 --> 00:36:49.957
I. erm... I have my letter-writing to do. I...

565
00:36:51.560 --> 00:36:55.633
I'll read to you tomorrow.
Goodnight. my dears.

566
00:37:01.160 --> 00:37:02.149
Evangeline.

567
00:37:02.360 --> 00:37:06.114
please ask Cook to make the children
scrambled eggs on toast.

568
00:37:06.320 --> 00:37:09.118
I'm sure they'd like supper
now they're feeling better.

569
00:37:09.320 --> 00:37:12.357
I'll do it myself. Nanny McPhee.

570
00:37:16.120 --> 00:37:19.954
- [clears throat gently]
- [tinkling breeze sighs]

571
00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:22.116
Didn't she have two bumpy things?

572
00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:24.311
The word is "wart".

573
00:37:24.520 --> 00:37:27.990
Traditionally associated with witches.
as it happens.

574
00:37:28.200 --> 00:37:30.475
Well. one of 'em's gone.

575
00:37:38.760 --> 00:37:41.513
- [magical wind rushes]
- [gasps]

576
00:37:41.720 --> 00:37:43.631
I did knock.

577
00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:45.751
Of course you did.

578
00:37:45.960 --> 00:37:49.839
Lesson two. to get up when they're told.
is complete.

579
00:37:50.040 --> 00:37:52.076
Of course. Very good. Thank you.

580
00:37:52.280 --> 00:37:54.316
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

581
00:37:55.760 --> 00:37:58.194
- Nanny McPhee...
- Yes. Mr Brown?

582
00:37:58.400 --> 00:38:00.595
Didn't you used to have two...

583
00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:04.909
w...w...?

584
00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:10.752
Never mind. It's. er... it's my imagination.

585
00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:16.549
[church bell tolls]

586
00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:22.553
There was a telegram. Mr Brown.

587
00:38:30.600 --> 00:38:32.875
Oh. my... Oh. my goodness.

588
00:38:36.200 --> 00:38:38.111
- Ah. Nanny McPhee.
- Pa!

589
00:38:38.320 --> 00:38:41.869
Good. good. good.
All right. I have an announcement.

590
00:38:42.080 --> 00:38:43.479
Yes...

591
00:38:43.680 --> 00:38:46.638
Your Great-Aunt Adelaide
is coming for tea today.

592
00:38:46.840 --> 00:38:48.159
[grizzles]

593
00:38:48.360 --> 00:38:50.999
- No!
- Aunt Adelaide is vile and vicious.

594
00:38:51.200 --> 00:38:54.510
She's blind as a bat.
And we are convalescing. for heaven's sake!

595
00:38:54.720 --> 00:38:58.998
That's enough. I don't want to hear
anything bad about her. She pays the rent.

596
00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:02.510
- She scares me.
- She's only coming for tea.

597
00:39:02.720 --> 00:39:04.950
You'll all put your best clothes on

598
00:39:05.160 --> 00:39:07.549
and Nanny McPhee will keep you in order.

599
00:39:07.760 --> 00:39:11.912
I shall do my best. sir.
considering that today is Sunday

600
00:39:12.120 --> 00:39:14.156
and I am off duty this afternoon.

601
00:39:14.360 --> 00:39:15.998
- [jingle]
- Off duty?

602
00:39:16.200 --> 00:39:18.031
- [rattle jingles]
- Mm.

603
00:39:18.240 --> 00:39:20.629
- [rattle jingles]
- You're off duty when...?

604
00:39:20.840 --> 00:39:23.673
You can't be off duty.
I need you. They need you.

605
00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:25.757
- [jingle]
- I shall be leaving at noon.

606
00:39:25.960 --> 00:39:31.273
Thereafter. I'm sure the children will do
exactly as they're told. Won't you. children?

607
00:39:32.920 --> 00:39:35.912
Listen to this. dear. Aunt Adelaide says.

608
00:39:36.120 --> 00:39:38.554
"l am coming with the express intention

609
00:39:38.760 --> 00:39:41.638
of easing your financial burden."

610
00:39:41.840 --> 00:39:45.799
Maybe she's thought the better
of my having to remarry.

611
00:39:46.000 --> 00:39:48.673
Perhaps I won't have to go through with it.

612
00:39:48.880 --> 00:39:51.314
[whinnies]

613
00:39:52.320 --> 00:39:55.790
- [coachman] Yah! Yah!
- [whinnying]

614
00:40:04.880 --> 00:40:08.111
[Sebastian] I hate my best clothes.
They're itchy.

615
00:40:08.320 --> 00:40:10.276
Well. we promised. so that's that.

616
00:40:11.320 --> 00:40:14.392
Tora's right.
We should do exactly as we're told.

617
00:40:14.600 --> 00:40:18.559
We've been told to put
our best clothes on. haven't we? Right.

618
00:40:18.760 --> 00:40:23.675
Well. I'm going to put
my best clothes on...the pig.

619
00:40:23.880 --> 00:40:25.108
Simon. no.

620
00:40:25.320 --> 00:40:28.790
- Yeah. the pig!
- Oh. please. don't!

621
00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:35.758
[horses snort]

622
00:40:35.960 --> 00:40:39.077
- Aunt Adelaide. welcome back.
- Where are you?

623
00:40:39.280 --> 00:40:42.431
- Here I am. Aunt Adelaide.
- Oh! Don't crowd me so.

624
00:40:42.640 --> 00:40:46.633
You're looking very peely-wally.
Where's my tea? I must have tea.

625
00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:48.432
Of course. This way. At once.

626
00:40:50.040 --> 00:40:51.473
I smell damp.

627
00:40:51.680 --> 00:40:55.229
[sniffs] No. no... At least not noticeably.

628
00:40:55.440 --> 00:40:57.874
Damp in the house.
Hence your pallid complexion.

629
00:40:58.080 --> 00:40:59.035
Lovely hat.

630
00:40:59.240 --> 00:41:02.915
A gift from the Duchess of Kent.
She has taste.

631
00:41:03.120 --> 00:41:06.032
- I've always hated this room.
- [chuckles]

632
00:41:06.240 --> 00:41:07.719
- Milk?
- Certainly not.

633
00:41:07.920 --> 00:41:10.150
Filthy stuff. Most unhealthy.

634
00:41:10.360 --> 00:41:12.590
- Sugar?
- Six. if you please.

635
00:41:12.800 --> 00:41:14.279
Six.

636
00:41:14.480 --> 00:41:19.349
Let me not beat about the bush. Cedric.
You have too many children.

637
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.869
- Ah. that.
- Don't interrupt.

638
00:41:22.080 --> 00:41:27.154
Your wife. my poor. weak-minded niece.
had no sense of proportion.

639
00:41:27.360 --> 00:41:32.275
However. I know where my duties lie.
I gave her my word that I would help.

640
00:41:32.480 --> 00:41:35.517
As you know. Cedric. my word is my law.

641
00:41:35.720 --> 00:41:38.029
I now propose to help you further.

642
00:41:38.240 --> 00:41:43.155
- Oh. thank you. Aunt Adelaide. Thank you.
- Don't interrupt. Sit down.

643
00:41:43.360 --> 00:41:45.874
This is my proposal.

644
00:41:46.080 --> 00:41:49.595
I shall relieve you of one of your children...

645
00:41:50.640 --> 00:41:53.518
and give it a home with me at Stitch Manor.

646
00:41:53.720 --> 00:41:55.756
[thunderclap]

647
00:41:55.960 --> 00:41:57.109
[gasps]

648
00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:01.797
It will require sacrifice on my part.
I realise that.

649
00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:07.711
But as my sainted father always said.
"Duty. Adelaide. always duty."

650
00:42:07.920 --> 00:42:11.356
- You mustn't. I can't possibly...
- Thank me enough. I know.

651
00:42:11.560 --> 00:42:15.155
You must feel quite overwhelmed
by the benefits of such a plan.

652
00:42:15.360 --> 00:42:16.952
Your fortunate daughter.

653
00:42:17.160 --> 00:42:20.596
for it must be a girl
and not one of those other things.

654
00:42:20.800 --> 00:42:24.554
will receive private tuition
in literature. history. deportment

655
00:42:24.760 --> 00:42:27.911
and above all. elocution.

656
00:42:28.120 --> 00:42:33.274
If there's one thing I won't stand for.
it's loose vowels.

657
00:42:34.680 --> 00:42:38.798
What did Papa say? He must have
told her not to even think of it.

658
00:42:39.000 --> 00:42:41.355
He didn't say anything.

659
00:42:42.400 --> 00:42:44.550
[Tora sighs]

660
00:42:44.760 --> 00:42:47.991
Come on. Let's find the others.

661
00:42:48.200 --> 00:42:51.636
I must be frank.
There is no question of your taking...

662
00:42:51.840 --> 00:42:57.039
Hush now! I'm used to taking responsibility
for other people's mistakes.

663
00:42:57.240 --> 00:43:01.677
Now. where is the bulk of your offspring?

664
00:43:07.840 --> 00:43:11.674
- Ah. Here we are.
- [oinks]

665
00:43:14.440 --> 00:43:16.590
- Oh!
- Baaagh!

666
00:43:16.800 --> 00:43:19.917
- It was a bee. A big bee. Erm...
- Good heavens!

667
00:43:21.960 --> 00:43:23.996
Gone now. Phew.

668
00:43:24.200 --> 00:43:27.237
- Hm.
- You're not well. Cedric.

669
00:43:27.440 --> 00:43:30.716
The sooner you find a good wife. the better.

670
00:43:30.920 --> 00:43:34.595
- [brays]
- This'll put her off wanting any of you girls.

671
00:43:34.800 --> 00:43:37.598
- [oinks]
- Speak up. girl!

672
00:43:37.800 --> 00:43:41.395
Oh! What an unfortunate face.

673
00:43:41.600 --> 00:43:44.478
All those bristles.

674
00:43:44.680 --> 00:43:47.877
It might be very hard
to get her decently betrothed.

675
00:43:48.080 --> 00:43:50.071
[oinking]

676
00:43:50.280 --> 00:43:52.635
Do you not have a more comely girl?

677
00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:54.990
[panting]

678
00:43:55.200 --> 00:43:58.078
[clucking]

679
00:43:58.280 --> 00:44:01.556
- Erm... perhaps round the front of the house.
- Oh!

680
00:44:01.760 --> 00:44:03.796
[pig oinks]

681
00:44:05.120 --> 00:44:08.476
- [brays]
- Chrissie. hurry up!

682
00:44:10.800 --> 00:44:13.234
- Tie it. Chrissie.
- [braying]

683
00:44:13.440 --> 00:44:16.273
- [shrieks]
- [Simon] Eric. stop her!

684
00:44:16.480 --> 00:44:18.357
- Chrissie. stop! She'll see you!
- Papa!

685
00:44:18.560 --> 00:44:21.711
Cedric. I had no idea
that you had produced such a...

686
00:44:21.920 --> 00:44:25.276
such an unattractive batch of females.

687
00:44:25.480 --> 00:44:29.234
I shall leave directly. Get my hat.

688
00:44:29.440 --> 00:44:31.954
Your hat? So soon?

689
00:44:32.160 --> 00:44:34.958
- Really? No. you can't... I'll get it.
- Hewitt!

690
00:44:37.640 --> 00:44:39.153
No!

691
00:44:41.800 --> 00:44:43.358
- A-ha!
- [gasps]

692
00:44:43.560 --> 00:44:47.348
Oh. yes. You'll do perfectly.

693
00:44:47.560 --> 00:44:52.270
A little timid. perhaps.
but we'll soon knock that out of you.

694
00:44:52.480 --> 00:44:55.597
Come on. come on. It can't do any harm to try.

695
00:44:55.800 --> 00:44:58.519
I can't find your... What are you doing?

696
00:44:58.720 --> 00:45:00.950
- This is the chosen one. Get her ready.
- Papa. help!

697
00:45:01.160 --> 00:45:05.119
- Chrissie? You're not listen...
- Shut up. Cedric. and do as you're told!

698
00:45:05.320 --> 00:45:08.471
Nanny McPhee. we need you.

699
00:45:08.680 --> 00:45:14.073
- Nanny McPhee. please. we need you.
- [magical wind rushes]

700
00:45:14.280 --> 00:45:18.114
- Where is my hat?
- [donkey braying]

701
00:45:18.320 --> 00:45:20.197
[brays triumphantly]

702
00:45:20.400 --> 00:45:21.753
Hide!

703
00:45:27.400 --> 00:45:29.277
My hat!

704
00:45:29.480 --> 00:45:32.552
- How dare you!
- [creaking]

705
00:45:32.760 --> 00:45:37.436
- [crashing thud]
- [brays]

706
00:45:39.600 --> 00:45:41.591
[chuckles]

707
00:45:41.800 --> 00:45:45.873
- Oh. my. what a merry game.
- Yoo-hoo!

708
00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:48.548
My. my. what a pretty girl you are.

709
00:45:52.600 --> 00:45:55.558
[donkey whistles merry tune]

710
00:45:55.760 --> 00:45:58.194
Oh. this is the girl for me.

711
00:45:59.640 --> 00:46:01.119
Run.

712
00:46:01.320 --> 00:46:04.437
Such poise. such gaiety.

713
00:46:04.640 --> 00:46:07.552
- Ah. there you are. staff.
- Yes. madam.

714
00:46:07.760 --> 00:46:11.673
I'm taking this child with me. Get her ready.

715
00:46:11.880 --> 00:46:14.030
[blows smoochy kiss]

716
00:46:18.480 --> 00:46:19.913
Very well. madam.

717
00:46:20.120 --> 00:46:22.395
Sherry time.

718
00:46:22.600 --> 00:46:24.795
[magical breeze sighs]

719
00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:28.879
Do not forget that someone
has to go with your great-aunt

720
00:46:29.080 --> 00:46:31.469
and it cannot be the donkey. can it?

721
00:46:36.320 --> 00:46:38.515
[birds caw]

722
00:46:41.360 --> 00:46:44.477
[Tora] Well. I'm the eldest girl. I'll go.

723
00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:49.470
[Lily] No. I've always known
I was destined for tragedy. I'll go.

724
00:46:49.680 --> 00:46:51.432
[Aggy] Aggy go.

725
00:46:51.640 --> 00:46:55.076
[Eric] Don't be silly. Aggy.
You're not even a whole girl yet.

726
00:46:56.200 --> 00:46:59.192
[Chrissie] No. She wanted me. I'll go.

727
00:46:59.400 --> 00:47:01.436
[Sebastian] You can't all go.

728
00:47:12.320 --> 00:47:14.993
Well. I am entirely satisfied.

729
00:47:15.200 --> 00:47:19.557
I will keep my word. Cedric.
if you will keep yours.

730
00:47:19.760 --> 00:47:23.275
You must give those children a mother
before the month is out.

731
00:47:23.480 --> 00:47:24.833
No.

732
00:47:26.640 --> 00:47:27.834
What?

733
00:47:28.040 --> 00:47:32.158
You cannot order me around. And you
certainly can't take any of my children.

734
00:47:32.360 --> 00:47:33.873
- l...
- [magical breeze blows]

735
00:47:34.080 --> 00:47:37.675
Your carriage awaits. madam.

736
00:47:37.880 --> 00:47:39.871
Is the chosen one seated?

737
00:47:40.080 --> 00:47:43.072
- lndeed she is.
- Good.

738
00:47:43.280 --> 00:47:46.750
- All is prepared.
- Which chosen one? What's prepared?

739
00:47:46.960 --> 00:47:49.633
Cedric. in view of this afternoon's
happy outcome.

740
00:47:49.840 --> 00:47:53.355
I am willing to overlook
that last unattractive outburst.

741
00:47:53.560 --> 00:47:55.915
- Nanny McPhee.
- Off we go. Hewitt.

742
00:47:56.120 --> 00:47:58.873
- What have you done?
- I have done nothing. sir.

743
00:47:59.080 --> 00:48:01.469
The children have decided
amongst themselves.

744
00:48:01.680 --> 00:48:03.750
Decided what? What do you mean?

745
00:48:03.960 --> 00:48:05.916
[Adelaide] There you are. dear.

746
00:48:06.120 --> 00:48:09.192
- Not little Chrissie.
- [coachman cracks whip] Yah!

747
00:48:10.280 --> 00:48:11.872
Chrissie!

748
00:48:13.600 --> 00:48:14.999
- [coachman] Yah!
- [whinnying]

749
00:48:15.200 --> 00:48:16.553
Chrissie!

750
00:48:17.760 --> 00:48:18.875
Yah!

751
00:48:20.520 --> 00:48:21.873
Chrissie!

752
00:48:26.440 --> 00:48:29.318
Now. then. you'd better
tell me your name. little girl.

753
00:48:29.520 --> 00:48:31.158
[bleating]

754
00:48:31.360 --> 00:48:32.998
- [whip cracks]
- Yah!

755
00:48:33.200 --> 00:48:37.034
- Christianna!
- Don't be shy. my dear. What is your name?

756
00:48:37.240 --> 00:48:39.549
- [shrill whinny]
- Yah!

757
00:48:40.920 --> 00:48:43.559
Sit up straight and tell me your name.

758
00:48:45.800 --> 00:48:47.791
No!

759
00:48:49.040 --> 00:48:50.917
- Christianna!
- Papa!

760
00:48:51.120 --> 00:48:53.793
Papa! Papa!

761
00:48:56.400 --> 00:48:59.198
Oh! [murmurs]

762
00:49:02.980 --> 00:49:04.459
Then...then who...?

763
00:49:08.140 --> 00:49:11.735
Evangeline. My name's Evangeline.

764
00:49:14.900 --> 00:49:16.174
[crashing thud]

765
00:49:16.380 --> 00:49:19.656
- [magical wind blows]
- [chuckles]

766
00:49:19.860 --> 00:49:23.694
And what a pretty name it is. too.

767
00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:28.930
Evangeline...

768
00:49:30.580 --> 00:49:32.013
Oh.

769
00:49:36.540 --> 00:49:40.294
- [horse whinnies]
- Yah! Yah!

770
00:49:49.780 --> 00:49:51.816
[tinkling breeze blows]

771
00:49:53.660 --> 00:49:55.969
Time for bed.

772
00:49:56.180 --> 00:49:59.855
- Thank you for saving me. Nanny McPhee.
- Hm.

773
00:50:01.620 --> 00:50:04.293
Yes. Thank you.

774
00:50:04.500 --> 00:50:06.616
Thank you.

775
00:50:06.820 --> 00:50:09.050
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

776
00:50:18.300 --> 00:50:21.133
[magical breeze blows]

777
00:50:24.860 --> 00:50:26.259
Hm.

778
00:50:28.380 --> 00:50:31.053
Papa was going to let her take me.

779
00:50:31.260 --> 00:50:35.890
No. Christianna.
Your father would never have allowed it.

780
00:50:43.380 --> 00:50:47.009
- Goodnight. children.
- [children] Goodnight. Nanny McPhee.

781
00:50:47.740 --> 00:50:49.856
[magical breeze sighs]

782
00:50:51.300 --> 00:50:53.495
She hasn't got any warts at all now.

783
00:50:53.700 --> 00:50:56.453
Do you think she's using
some sort of cream?

784
00:50:57.780 --> 00:51:00.977
[clock chimes]

785
00:51:18.700 --> 00:51:21.089
[magical wind rushes]

786
00:51:23.460 --> 00:51:26.816
Thank you. Nanny McPhee.
You were a tremendous help.

787
00:51:27.020 --> 00:51:28.248
Not at all.

788
00:51:28.460 --> 00:51:30.451
You will find that lesson three.

789
00:51:30.660 --> 00:51:33.936
to get dressed when they're told.
is complete.

790
00:51:34.140 --> 00:51:39.134
Just to get dressed when they're told?
They've learned a great deal more than that.

791
00:51:40.700 --> 00:51:42.770
I have five lessons to teach.

792
00:51:42.980 --> 00:51:47.337
What lessons they learn is entirely
up to them. Goodnight. Mr Brown.

793
00:51:47.540 --> 00:51:51.294
- Nanny McPhee...
- Yes. Mr Brown?

794
00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:55.698
She will be all right. won't she?
Evangeline. I mean.

795
00:51:57.180 --> 00:52:00.172
I can't help being concerned.

796
00:52:00.380 --> 00:52:04.259
Aunt Adelaide can be so. erm...
Well. you saw.

797
00:52:04.460 --> 00:52:06.849
She will certainly be all right.

798
00:52:07.060 --> 00:52:09.494
Good.

799
00:52:09.700 --> 00:52:14.455
I suppose she volunteered to go. did she?
Couldn't wait to be shot of us. I imagine.

800
00:52:14.660 --> 00:52:16.412
Not quite.

801
00:52:16.620 --> 00:52:18.099
It was Simon's idea.

802
00:52:18.300 --> 00:52:20.689
He knew Evangeline
might like to educate herself

803
00:52:20.900 --> 00:52:23.937
and that her going would save Christianna.

804
00:52:24.140 --> 00:52:25.858
He's a very clever boy.

805
00:52:26.060 --> 00:52:31.418
Good heavens. Simon. eh?
Well. good for him. Quick...quick thinking.

806
00:52:31.620 --> 00:52:33.815
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

807
00:52:39.020 --> 00:52:41.170
[sighs deeply]

808
00:52:47.620 --> 00:52:50.088
So that's it. then.

809
00:52:50.300 --> 00:52:53.133
I shall have to marry...Quickly.

810
00:53:26.140 --> 00:53:28.973
[magical breeze zings and whooshes]

811
00:53:31.540 --> 00:53:34.259
[Sebastian laughs]

812
00:53:42.180 --> 00:53:43.579
[clears throat]

813
00:53:43.780 --> 00:53:46.977
Children. your father has asked me to tell you

814
00:53:47.180 --> 00:53:50.889
there's a Mrs Quickly coming for tea tomorrow.

815
00:53:51.940 --> 00:53:55.694
- Nanny McPhee?
- Yes. sweetheart?

816
00:53:55.900 --> 00:54:00.098
Can you stop Papa
from marrying a horrible stepmother?

817
00:54:02.140 --> 00:54:03.778
I'm afraid not.

818
00:54:03.980 --> 00:54:09.100
- Even if you wanted to?
- Even if I wanted to.

819
00:54:09.300 --> 00:54:13.976
I cannot interfere with affairs of the heart.

820
00:54:21.180 --> 00:54:23.535
Perhaps Simon could talk to him about it.

821
00:54:23.740 --> 00:54:25.856
He won't listen.

822
00:54:28.260 --> 00:54:31.013
[seagull cries]

823
00:54:36.980 --> 00:54:39.130
You have a visitor. Mr Brown.

824
00:54:39.340 --> 00:54:42.776
An especially eager visitor. Mr Brown.

825
00:54:51.860 --> 00:54:55.170
Quickly by name...

826
00:54:55.380 --> 00:54:56.449
Oh!

827
00:54:56.660 --> 00:54:58.730
Simon. my boy.

828
00:54:58.940 --> 00:55:01.090
Well. come in.

829
00:55:01.300 --> 00:55:03.177
Come on. I won't bite.

830
00:55:06.100 --> 00:55:09.979
- Father. we want to ask you something.
- Well. of course.

831
00:55:10.180 --> 00:55:12.136
Of course. Anything at all. Ask away.

832
00:55:12.340 --> 00:55:14.934
Who is Mrs Quickly?

833
00:55:16.420 --> 00:55:20.095
[chuckles feebly]
Good heavens. such a face. She's. er...

834
00:55:20.300 --> 00:55:22.939
She's...she's a friend. She's...a friend.

835
00:55:23.140 --> 00:55:24.971
Just a friend?

836
00:55:25.180 --> 00:55:28.411
Well. my boy.
it's not exactly any of your business. is it?

837
00:55:28.620 --> 00:55:30.770
It is if she's to be our new mother.

838
00:55:30.980 --> 00:55:32.698
Who said anything about that?

839
00:55:32.900 --> 00:55:35.698
It is true? You are going to marry her?

840
00:55:37.300 --> 00:55:38.972
You go too far. Simon.

841
00:55:39.180 --> 00:55:41.569
- You must not question...
- I didn't.

842
00:55:41.780 --> 00:55:43.418
- Don't contradict me!
- I'm not!

843
00:55:43.620 --> 00:55:46.418
You do not understand the adult world.

844
00:55:46.620 --> 00:55:49.453
You know. there are certain things that...

845
00:55:49.660 --> 00:55:52.254
certain things...

846
00:55:52.460 --> 00:55:54.735
You will leave me this instant. Go home!

847
00:55:57.380 --> 00:55:59.336
You never listen!

848
00:56:01.340 --> 00:56:03.012
[door slams]

849
00:56:27.620 --> 00:56:29.531
Nanny McPhee?

850
00:56:32.300 --> 00:56:34.336
Nanny McPhee?

851
00:56:40.020 --> 00:56:42.739
[creaking]

852
00:56:47.940 --> 00:56:50.408
[crystalline tinkling]

853
00:57:01.620 --> 00:57:03.815
[floorboard creaks]

854
00:57:34.220 --> 00:57:36.051
[crashing thud]

855
00:57:36.260 --> 00:57:38.535
Hello. Simon.

856
00:57:38.740 --> 00:57:40.253
Can I help you?

857
00:57:40.460 --> 00:57:42.496
I did knock.

858
00:57:42.700 --> 00:57:45.772
I know. I heard you.

859
00:57:49.220 --> 00:57:51.529
May I be of assistance?

860
00:57:52.620 --> 00:57:54.895
Er...

861
00:57:55.100 --> 00:57:58.172
We need you to. erm...

862
00:57:58.380 --> 00:58:00.689
I mean...you saved Chrissie.

863
00:58:01.740 --> 00:58:03.492
And so...

864
00:58:03.700 --> 00:58:06.453
You're on our side. is what I mean.

865
00:58:06.660 --> 00:58:08.537
Aren't you?

866
00:58:08.740 --> 00:58:13.256
You saved Chrissie. and I do not take sides.

867
00:58:15.060 --> 00:58:21.010
I...we... need you to help us
get rid of this woman. Mrs Quickly.

868
00:58:21.220 --> 00:58:26.533
It will not surprise you to hear
that I cannot agree to that. Simon.

869
00:58:26.740 --> 00:58:30.494
Then let us do whatever
we have to do to get rid of her.

870
00:58:30.700 --> 00:58:34.375
Are you prepared to accept
the consequences?

871
00:58:34.580 --> 00:58:35.899
Yes.

872
00:58:36.100 --> 00:58:39.888
- You promise?
- Yes. Yes. absolutely. I promise.

873
00:58:41.660 --> 00:58:43.013
Hm.

874
00:58:43.220 --> 00:58:48.977
Then I will. as you put it.
let you do whatever you have to do.

875
00:58:49.180 --> 00:58:50.898
Thank you.

876
00:58:52.620 --> 00:58:55.009
Thank you.

877
00:58:55.300 --> 00:58:57.211
- [honking]
- [screeches] Aaah!

878
00:58:57.420 --> 00:59:01.652
Look at them! Will you just look at them?

879
00:59:01.860 --> 00:59:03.578
Aw!

880
00:59:03.780 --> 00:59:07.773
The little. small things.

881
00:59:08.900 --> 00:59:11.209
Children. this is. er... Mrs Quickly.

882
00:59:11.420 --> 00:59:13.331
Oh. you mustn't be so formal.

883
00:59:13.540 --> 00:59:17.818
You must call me Auntie Selma.

884
00:59:18.020 --> 00:59:21.615
Oh. dear me. one does work up
such a thirst in this heat.

885
00:59:22.900 --> 00:59:25.209
Oh. Tea. of course. Do go through. I'll...

886
00:59:25.420 --> 00:59:29.299
And leave these dear creatures?
How can you ask it of me?

887
00:59:31.260 --> 00:59:34.491
- Oh. the heart of the house.
- Yes. yes.

888
00:59:34.700 --> 00:59:36.850
- The old bachelor's den.
- Mm.

889
00:59:37.060 --> 00:59:40.132
- Well. l...
- lsn't it enchanting?

890
00:59:40.340 --> 00:59:42.535
Ooh! Have you read all those books?

891
00:59:42.740 --> 00:59:44.696
- Well. l. er...
- Clever.

892
00:59:44.900 --> 00:59:48.939
- Take my chair. It's more comfortable.
- Thank you. Ooh!

893
00:59:49.140 --> 00:59:51.813
Well. what have we here?

894
00:59:52.020 --> 00:59:56.616
I see there is already provision for a lady.
How thoughtful you are.

895
00:59:56.820 --> 00:59:58.776
What a gentleman.

896
01:00:00.620 --> 01:00:04.454
Wait! Er...just let me
make it. er...comfy for you.

897
01:00:04.660 --> 01:00:06.173
Too. too precious.

898
01:00:06.380 --> 01:00:09.975
Here in the centre of the male dominion.

899
01:00:10.180 --> 01:00:13.411
- [boing!]
-..an oasis of feminine charm and elegance.

900
01:00:13.620 --> 01:00:17.818
There. just as I thought. It's dusty.
It just needs a good old thump.

901
01:00:18.020 --> 01:00:20.978
There. All thumped and ready to go.

902
01:00:21.180 --> 01:00:25.332
There you go again.
Nothing is too much trouble for you.

903
01:00:26.500 --> 01:00:31.096
I observed that very characteristic
on the sad day we buried Mr Quickly.

904
01:00:31.300 --> 01:00:34.610
Even in my demented grief.
I said to my friend Letitia Carter...

905
01:00:34.820 --> 01:00:39.177
Remember her? A pinker complexion
than my own. She takes too much sun.

906
01:00:39.380 --> 01:00:43.214
I said. "Kindness seems to be
second nature to him."

907
01:00:43.420 --> 01:00:45.331
"He is a perfect gentleman."

908
01:00:45.540 --> 01:00:49.374
"There's something so masculine
and yet retiring in his manner..."

909
01:00:49.580 --> 01:00:51.332
[squeals] Mr Brown!

910
01:00:51.540 --> 01:00:54.498
[she giggles]

911
01:00:56.620 --> 01:00:58.576
- Urgh.
- Un moment. I pray you.

912
01:00:58.780 --> 01:01:00.657
I don't know what came over me.

913
01:01:00.860 --> 01:01:04.933
I do. I understand. I never took you for such.

914
01:01:05.140 --> 01:01:09.736
But now I see it.
Passion is clearly your nature. too.

915
01:01:09.940 --> 01:01:14.855
I feel it. Who would have thought
we were such kindred spirits?

916
01:01:15.060 --> 01:01:20.009
Passion is my life.
In fact. Mr Brown. what is life without it?

917
01:01:20.220 --> 01:01:24.611
- Er...
- A grey wheel of habit. spinning idly on.

918
01:01:26.340 --> 01:01:29.457
- Mmm!
- [giggles]

919
01:01:29.660 --> 01:01:32.299
[Mrs Quickly] Mmm!

920
01:01:32.500 --> 01:01:36.732
- This is no time for food. Mrs Quickly...
- Selma.

921
01:01:36.940 --> 01:01:39.613
I couldn't possibly swallow it
under the circumstances.

922
01:01:39.820 --> 01:01:42.129
You are tempestuous. Mr Brown.

923
01:01:43.300 --> 01:01:46.372
- Tea?
- Yes. tea.

924
01:01:46.580 --> 01:01:50.129
We must blanket the raw impulse
with that reliable beverage.

925
01:01:50.340 --> 01:01:52.171
[croaks]

926
01:01:53.380 --> 01:01:57.817
That's a nice bit of porcelain. Is that Spode?
I like a bit of Spode. Tasteful.

927
01:01:58.020 --> 01:02:01.490
Anyway. so essential
for upholding the normal...

928
01:02:01.700 --> 01:02:04.976
- You don't want that.
- How right you are.

929
01:02:05.180 --> 01:02:07.740
You see into my inmost self.

930
01:02:07.940 --> 01:02:12.536
What is tea when we can drink
from the nectar of our emotions?

931
01:02:12.740 --> 01:02:14.492
Let the common herd drink tea.

932
01:02:14.700 --> 01:02:18.295
Our souls need a more divine libation!

933
01:02:18.980 --> 01:02:21.050
- [wibbling]
- Whoa...whoo-ow!

934
01:02:22.700 --> 01:02:25.772
Oh! You mad fool! I say.

935
01:02:25.980 --> 01:02:28.699
No. no. not here amongst the cutlery.

936
01:02:28.900 --> 01:02:31.095
- I say! [giggles]
- [rattling]

937
01:02:32.660 --> 01:02:35.936
I must go before my reputation
is in tatters on this rug.

938
01:02:36.140 --> 01:02:38.256
Lovely rug. Is it Chinese silk?

939
01:02:38.460 --> 01:02:40.928
Must escape before all is lost.

940
01:02:41.140 --> 01:02:42.414
Wait!

941
01:02:42.620 --> 01:02:46.898
Heavens to Betsy! You are inflamed!

942
01:02:47.100 --> 01:02:51.571
How does a lonely widow best you?
What defences does she have?

943
01:02:53.260 --> 01:02:56.058
All it takes is one question. Cedric.
and I'm yours.

944
01:02:56.260 --> 01:03:01.334
- Ask me or you'll lose me forever.
- Oh. no... Absolutely.

945
01:03:01.540 --> 01:03:04.008
[Mrs Quickly] Say it. Say it.

946
01:03:04.220 --> 01:03:07.895
- Say it. Say it.
- No!

947
01:03:08.580 --> 01:03:12.892
Oh! No! This is too much. sir!

948
01:03:14.220 --> 01:03:16.256
You are a cad!

949
01:03:18.060 --> 01:03:21.177
A bounder and a cad! [sobs]

950
01:03:21.940 --> 01:03:24.659
- [children giggle]
- Yeah!

951
01:03:24.860 --> 01:03:26.657
[Simon] Papa's coming.

952
01:03:37.860 --> 01:03:40.579
She's gone.

953
01:03:40.780 --> 01:03:45.058
The only person in the whole world
who stands between all of us

954
01:03:45.260 --> 01:03:47.820
and total ruin...

955
01:03:48.020 --> 01:03:50.773
and she's gone.

956
01:03:52.260 --> 01:03:54.296
What's ruin?

957
01:03:55.740 --> 01:04:00.177
There's no time to mince words.
I can't support my own family.

958
01:04:00.380 --> 01:04:03.816
I never have been able to.
There are so many of you.

959
01:04:05.100 --> 01:04:07.056
But you're all so delicious.

960
01:04:07.260 --> 01:04:10.536
When Aggy came along
and your mother was so ill. I said.

961
01:04:10.740 --> 01:04:14.892
"We may have to stop now. dear."
and she said...

962
01:04:15.100 --> 01:04:17.489
She said. "l know."

963
01:04:24.820 --> 01:04:27.812
The fact of the matter is.
your Great-Aunt Adelaide

964
01:04:28.020 --> 01:04:31.774
has been supporting us for years
with a monthly allowance.

965
01:04:31.980 --> 01:04:34.289
A little while ago. she told me

966
01:04:34.500 --> 01:04:37.537
that I had to remarry
or the allowance would stop.

967
01:04:37.740 --> 01:04:40.618
This woman today was my last chance.

968
01:04:40.820 --> 01:04:42.856
Our last chance.

969
01:04:43.060 --> 01:04:44.732
Ours?

970
01:04:46.140 --> 01:04:49.655
When the money stops.
the house will be taken.

971
01:04:49.860 --> 01:04:53.136
Some of you will perhaps
be put into the workhouse.

972
01:04:53.340 --> 01:04:57.697
Some will be put into the care...
into the care of others.

973
01:04:58.740 --> 01:05:02.415
I don't know how many of you
will be allowed to stay together.

974
01:05:09.020 --> 01:05:10.976
I'm sorry to have failed you. children.

975
01:05:14.860 --> 01:05:17.328
You deserve so much better.

976
01:05:22.100 --> 01:05:25.979
- Do something.
- What would you suggest?

977
01:05:26.180 --> 01:05:30.890
Change what happened.
Bang your stick. Make it undo itself.

978
01:05:31.100 --> 01:05:33.216
I cannot. These were your actions.

979
01:05:33.420 --> 01:05:36.935
Simon promised that you would
accept the consequences.

980
01:05:37.140 --> 01:05:40.450
What shall we do?
Help us. Tell us what to do.

981
01:05:40.660 --> 01:05:45.051
- You must undo it for yourselves.
- How? How?

982
01:05:45.260 --> 01:05:47.490
Think.

983
01:05:47.700 --> 01:05:50.419
You are very clever. children.

984
01:05:50.620 --> 01:05:52.133
Think.

985
01:05:53.380 --> 01:05:55.450
[women cackle with laughter]

986
01:05:55.660 --> 01:06:00.176
- So. 'e was keen?
- Oh. Letty. he was in a maddened condition.

987
01:06:00.380 --> 01:06:03.417
He couldn't keep his hands off me.
But I held firm.

988
01:06:03.620 --> 01:06:08.250
I said. "Shedric..." I mean. "Cedric.
I have my reputation to uphold."

989
01:06:08.460 --> 01:06:11.258
"It's marriage or nothing.
What do you take me for?"

990
01:06:11.460 --> 01:06:12.688
- [knocking]
- "Some common...?"

991
01:06:12.900 --> 01:06:15.414
- Tart?
- Not for me. I'm bloated.

992
01:06:15.620 --> 01:06:17.895
- No. "Some common tart." You said...
- [knocking]

993
01:06:18.100 --> 01:06:20.773
- Who's that knocking?
- [lamb bleats]

994
01:06:20.980 --> 01:06:22.936
- It might be him.
- Ooh!

995
01:06:24.740 --> 01:06:27.891
If you've come to fumble
with my fastenings... Oh.

996
01:06:28.100 --> 01:06:29.215
[rattle jingles]

997
01:06:29.420 --> 01:06:33.379
Mrs Quickly. we're very sorry about the tea
you had with our father.

998
01:06:33.580 --> 01:06:37.095
Typical of a man. sending his little ones
to do the dirty work.

999
01:06:37.300 --> 01:06:39.734
No. He doesn't know we're...

1000
01:06:39.940 --> 01:06:42.329
I mean. he very much wants to marry you.

1001
01:06:42.540 --> 01:06:46.419
I know what he wanted.
No wonder there's so many of you (!)

1002
01:06:46.620 --> 01:06:50.932
Wait. Father wasn't being rude.
No one on earth could be less rude.

1003
01:06:51.140 --> 01:06:54.257
He was protecting you from
the naughty things we were doing.

1004
01:06:54.460 --> 01:06:57.452
- The toad in the teapot.
- And the wormy sandwiches.

1005
01:06:57.660 --> 01:07:00.970
That was my idea! I mean. my fault.

1006
01:07:01.180 --> 01:07:04.058
I have no idea to what you can be referring.

1007
01:07:04.260 --> 01:07:08.219
Don't try to make excuses for him.
He's a flounder and a gad.

1008
01:07:08.420 --> 01:07:11.776
He's not. He's a good man.
He was just trying to save us.

1009
01:07:11.980 --> 01:07:16.610
If he doesn't marry. all the money will go.
We'll be thrown out onto the streets.

1010
01:07:16.820 --> 01:07:20.529
- Money? What money?
- Our Great-Aunt Adelaide's money.

1011
01:07:20.740 --> 01:07:23.129
Lady Adelaide Stitch.

1012
01:07:23.340 --> 01:07:25.934
Lady? Ooh!

1013
01:07:27.180 --> 01:07:29.057
- Mr Brown.
- Mrs Quickly.

1014
01:07:29.260 --> 01:07:32.377
- Your children have explained it all.
- Explained?

1015
01:07:32.580 --> 01:07:36.368
That their tricks during tea was a result
of their motherless condition.

1016
01:07:36.580 --> 01:07:39.094
that they need a woman's presence
to calm them.

1017
01:07:39.300 --> 01:07:41.939
and that you could benefit from that presence.

1018
01:07:42.140 --> 01:07:44.210
pathetic and lonely as you are.

1019
01:07:44.420 --> 01:07:50.211
And all it takes is one little question. Cedric.
[clears throat]

1020
01:07:52.580 --> 01:07:55.617
Oh. Oh. y... er...yes. of course.

1021
01:07:55.820 --> 01:07:58.095
Erm...just give me...Yes.

1022
01:07:59.420 --> 01:08:01.251
- Mrs Quickly...
- [whispers] Selma.

1023
01:08:01.460 --> 01:08:03.257
Yes. I mean Selma.

1024
01:08:03.460 --> 01:08:07.453
Would you do me the honour
of becoming my...

1025
01:08:09.980 --> 01:08:12.733
-..of becoming my...
- Wife.

1026
01:08:12.940 --> 01:08:18.014
- Exactly. Wife. That's the word.
- Yes. Oh. yes. Cedric.

1027
01:08:18.900 --> 01:08:21.619
Mmm.... mwa!

1028
01:08:23.420 --> 01:08:26.093
Off you go now. dears.

1029
01:08:26.300 --> 01:08:31.010
Let Daddy have a little moment to himself
with your new mummy.

1030
01:08:34.860 --> 01:08:40.218
(Nanny McPhee) A bit big for this nightie. aren't
you. sweetheart? We'll have a new one made.

1031
01:08:49.660 --> 01:08:51.616
I'm sorry.

1032
01:08:53.860 --> 01:08:57.216
I should have told you. I can see that now.

1033
01:08:57.420 --> 01:09:01.129
If I'd discussed it with you before.
we wouldn't be in this mess.

1034
01:09:02.700 --> 01:09:05.533
No. it was our fault.

1035
01:09:07.900 --> 01:09:11.609
We should have known you had
a good reason for getting married.

1036
01:09:11.820 --> 01:09:17.895
At least this way. we'll all be together.
That's what matters most. isn't it? Hm?

1037
01:09:18.100 --> 01:09:21.331
I promise I'll never hide anything
that affects us from you again.

1038
01:09:21.540 --> 01:09:24.498
I see you're more than capable
of understanding it.

1039
01:09:25.980 --> 01:09:28.778
- Papa?
- Yes. my boy?

1040
01:09:28.980 --> 01:09:33.053
Do you think Mama still thinks about us
where she is?

1041
01:09:35.740 --> 01:09:37.890
I'm sure she does.

1042
01:09:39.700 --> 01:09:41.736
I know she does.

1043
01:09:47.100 --> 01:09:50.979
Now. Chrissie.
why don't you choose us a story?

1044
01:09:52.980 --> 01:09:55.448
[woman] ¢Ü Tiptoe by

1045
01:09:55.660 --> 01:09:59.050
- ¢Ü Where my babies lie...
- Lesson four is complete.

1046
01:09:59.260 --> 01:10:02.570
¢Ü In your tiny silver shoon...

1047
01:10:02.780 --> 01:10:05.089
Lesson four?

1048
01:10:06.420 --> 01:10:08.854
To listen.

1049
01:10:11.740 --> 01:10:13.298
Well done.

1050
01:10:13.500 --> 01:10:18.813
¢Ü Will you watch over. please

1051
01:10:19.020 --> 01:10:22.092
¢Ü My wee ones

1052
01:10:22.300 --> 01:10:25.576
¢Ü My lambkins

1053
01:10:25.780 --> 01:10:31.491
¢Ü My sweet chick-a-chickadees

1054
01:10:32.420 --> 01:10:38.097
¢Ü Loola-bye. oh. loola-bye

1055
01:10:39.140 --> 01:10:51.257
¢Ü In your tiny silver shoon ¢Ü

1056
01:10:52.780 --> 01:10:55.692
- [church bells ring]
- [lamb bleats]

1057
01:10:55.900 --> 01:10:58.778
[Mrs Quickly] The big day.
I do love my weddings.

1058
01:10:58.980 --> 01:11:01.448
Mr Brown. What's he really like?

1059
01:11:01.660 --> 01:11:04.254
No idea. Keen as mustard
to tie the knot. though.

1060
01:11:04.460 --> 01:11:08.055
Had to sort this out quick.
Only got the sheep dipped yesterday.

1061
01:11:08.260 --> 01:11:11.935
But he's easily controlled.
unlike his nasty little brood.

1062
01:11:12.140 --> 01:11:14.529
However will you manage them. Selma?

1063
01:11:14.740 --> 01:11:17.538
I've got a few tricks up my sleeve.
Never you mind.

1064
01:11:17.740 --> 01:11:20.573
I started off by giving them a good clean-up.

1065
01:11:20.780 --> 01:11:22.930
Oh. don't they look lovely?

1066
01:11:24.780 --> 01:11:27.453
Sebastian. your top button is undone.

1067
01:11:27.660 --> 01:11:31.812
Lily. you have a little hair caught
in your crook. Eric. help her. please.

1068
01:11:32.020 --> 01:11:34.739
Your father will be down in a moment.

1069
01:11:34.940 --> 01:11:39.411
Now. that is an improvement.
Letty. go and keep a lookout.

1070
01:11:40.340 --> 01:11:42.456
I say. whatever your name is.

1071
01:11:42.660 --> 01:11:45.652
give me a second on my own
with the little darlings?

1072
01:11:50.460 --> 01:11:55.090
Now. my dears. there's going to be
some changes made round here.

1073
01:11:56.700 --> 01:11:58.930
I'm in charge of this household now

1074
01:11:59.140 --> 01:12:03.452
and while I'm in charge.
you children will behave.

1075
01:12:03.660 --> 01:12:07.255
Do you hear? Behave.

1076
01:12:07.460 --> 01:12:11.658
- [Aggy jingles rattle]
- Behave.

1077
01:12:13.900 --> 01:12:18.815
And we're not having any of that nasty noise
all the way through my nice wedding.

1078
01:12:19.020 --> 01:12:23.730
- [grizzles uncertainly. then sobs]
- Shut her up.

1079
01:12:25.620 --> 01:12:27.212
Naughty.

1080
01:12:27.420 --> 01:12:29.615
It's our mother's rattle. Give it back.

1081
01:12:29.820 --> 01:12:31.890
I'm your mother now.

1082
01:12:37.300 --> 01:12:39.291
Time to adapt.

1083
01:12:41.100 --> 01:12:44.331
- [magical breeze sighs]
- Hm.

1084
01:12:44.540 --> 01:12:46.212
[footsteps]

1085
01:12:48.260 --> 01:12:50.251
- Papa. Mrs Quickly...
- Sh!

1086
01:12:50.460 --> 01:12:52.530
Yoo-hoo. Cedric.

1087
01:12:52.740 --> 01:12:56.130
I realise the bride and groom
shouldn't meet until the ceremony.

1088
01:12:56.340 --> 01:12:59.093
- but you and I are old hands at this.
- [hoofbeats]

1089
01:12:59.300 --> 01:13:03.259
- [horse whinnies]
- She's here! Lady Stitch!

1090
01:13:03.460 --> 01:13:05.052
Selma. there's footmen.

1091
01:13:06.980 --> 01:13:10.495
- [Cook sputters] Oi. make way!
- [Letty squeaks]

1092
01:13:14.020 --> 01:13:15.419
Where's the woman?

1093
01:13:15.620 --> 01:13:18.896
- Aunt Adelaide...
- Shut up! Where's the woman. Cedric?

1094
01:13:19.100 --> 01:13:23.457
May I present my...fiancee. Selma Quickly.
Selma. this is Lady Stitch.

1095
01:13:23.660 --> 01:13:27.369
Your Ladyness. Welcome. if I may be so bold.

1096
01:13:27.580 --> 01:13:30.048
to our humble. nay. lowly festivities.

1097
01:13:30.260 --> 01:13:33.332
You shower glory upon us from above.

1098
01:13:33.540 --> 01:13:37.215
The very air about you shines with...

1099
01:13:37.420 --> 01:13:41.413
with...with aboveness.

1100
01:13:41.620 --> 01:13:45.613
A gracious welcome. I must say.
Rise. my dear.

1101
01:13:45.820 --> 01:13:48.493
Here are the children
in their. erm...shepherdess outfits.

1102
01:13:48.700 --> 01:13:52.693
Well. that's the girls.
The boys... I'm not sure what they are.

1103
01:13:52.900 --> 01:13:54.856
But. erm...anyway. you can see.

1104
01:13:55.060 --> 01:13:57.130
Oh. keep up. will you?

1105
01:14:15.620 --> 01:14:17.531
[whispers] Who's that?

1106
01:14:17.740 --> 01:14:21.653
- It's a princess.
- A fairy princess.

1107
01:14:23.260 --> 01:14:25.899
It's Evangeline.

1108
01:14:28.540 --> 01:14:32.294
Straight back. Remember your vowels.

1109
01:14:33.580 --> 01:14:38.700
May I present my adopted daughter.
Miss Evangeline Stitch.

1110
01:14:42.580 --> 01:14:46.050
What are we doing milling about
in this dreary vestibule?

1111
01:14:46.260 --> 01:14:48.296
Sherry this instant.

1112
01:14:48.500 --> 01:14:52.812
Might I beg the honour of pouring
the privileged schooners myself?

1113
01:14:53.980 --> 01:14:56.972
[perfectly plummy]
Delectable to see you again. madam.

1114
01:14:57.180 --> 01:14:59.250
Blinkin' hell!

1115
01:15:01.380 --> 01:15:04.133
And how nice to see the young people.

1116
01:15:04.340 --> 01:15:08.299
Welcome back. Evangeline.
You look well. Are you well?

1117
01:15:08.500 --> 01:15:11.378
I am most content.

1118
01:15:12.620 --> 01:15:16.249
You must be very happy
to be marrying again.

1119
01:15:17.260 --> 01:15:21.970
Oh. yes. I'm... I'm...
How did you put it? Most content.

1120
01:15:22.180 --> 01:15:24.933
Of course. Good grief.

1121
01:15:26.500 --> 01:15:28.456
I am so glad.

1122
01:15:28.660 --> 01:15:30.730
- [Adelaide] Evangeline!
- [bell jangles]

1123
01:15:30.940 --> 01:15:33.408
Pray excuse me.

1124
01:15:35.740 --> 01:15:39.813
Are you sure it's Evangeline?
It doesn't look anything like her.

1125
01:15:40.020 --> 01:15:42.773
Nonsense. She's always looked like that.

1126
01:15:44.740 --> 01:15:47.573
[they play ¢Ü Here Comes The Bride]

1127
01:15:47.780 --> 01:15:49.372
[bleating]

1128
01:15:51.060 --> 01:15:53.620
[hums along]

1129
01:16:13.220 --> 01:16:16.610
What can we do?
There has to be another way.

1130
01:16:16.820 --> 01:16:19.892
- Behave.
- Beehive.

1131
01:16:20.100 --> 01:16:21.897
You must do as you're told.

1132
01:16:22.100 --> 01:16:24.330
- Behave.
- Beehive.

1133
01:16:24.540 --> 01:16:29.295
Lesson number five. Simon.
You must do exactly as you're told.

1134
01:16:31.700 --> 01:16:34.772
[violins crescendo]

1135
01:16:37.940 --> 01:16:39.612
Beehive.

1136
01:16:39.820 --> 01:16:41.139
Beehive?

1137
01:16:41.340 --> 01:16:42.978
Please be seated.

1138
01:16:44.700 --> 01:16:46.930
There isn't a beehive. What do you mean?

1139
01:16:50.060 --> 01:16:54.372
Dearly beloved. we are gathered here together

1140
01:16:54.580 --> 01:16:59.210
in the sight of God
and in the face of this congregation

1141
01:16:59.420 --> 01:17:03.538
to join together this man and this woman

1142
01:17:03.740 --> 01:17:06.573
in holy matrimony.

1143
01:17:06.780 --> 01:17:11.900
which is an honourable estate
instituted of God

1144
01:17:12.100 --> 01:17:14.933
in the time of man's innocence...

1145
01:17:17.340 --> 01:17:19.854
..and commended of St Paul...

1146
01:17:20.060 --> 01:17:23.257
- [children] Bzzzzzz!
-..to be honoured among all men.

1147
01:17:23.460 --> 01:17:25.052
Get off!

1148
01:17:25.260 --> 01:17:27.774
- And is therefore...
- Get off!

1149
01:17:27.980 --> 01:17:31.336
-.. not by any man to be enterprised...
- There's one on you!

1150
01:17:31.540 --> 01:17:36.819
.. nor taken in hand unadvisedly.
lightly. wantonly...

1151
01:17:37.700 --> 01:17:42.012
- There's one on your back!
-..to satisfy man's carnal lusts...

1152
01:17:42.220 --> 01:17:45.656
It's the flowers on her dress!
They're attracting them!

1153
01:17:45.860 --> 01:17:48.738
- I hate bees. I'm allergic.
- There aren't any bees. you fool!

1154
01:17:48.940 --> 01:17:51.579
No. truly. I swell up.

1155
01:17:51.780 --> 01:17:55.534
[hisses] They're trying to ruin
my lovely wedding. Nasty. vicious creatures.

1156
01:17:55.740 --> 01:17:58.254
- Do something!
- [children buzz energetically]

1157
01:17:59.900 --> 01:18:03.290
Cedric. look at me. Do you see any bees?

1158
01:18:03.500 --> 01:18:06.014
[other children buzzing]

1159
01:18:10.940 --> 01:18:15.536
I said. look at me!
Do you see any bees? Do you?

1160
01:18:15.740 --> 01:18:18.049
- Do you?
- I do.

1161
01:18:18.260 --> 01:18:22.731
- Ooaah!
- It's all right. I've got the little bugger.

1162
01:18:22.940 --> 01:18:25.374
[yelps] It's on me!

1163
01:18:25.580 --> 01:18:30.290
- [gasps]
- Lord love a duck! I'm so dreadfully sorry!

1164
01:18:30.500 --> 01:18:32.695
[children giggle]

1165
01:18:32.900 --> 01:18:34.538
No. no. no. no. no...

1166
01:18:37.780 --> 01:18:41.090
- [children laugh]
- Oh. my Lord. Your Higherness!

1167
01:19:01.300 --> 01:19:02.653
[gasps]

1168
01:19:07.260 --> 01:19:09.216
[both laugh uproariously]

1169
01:19:09.420 --> 01:19:12.412
- [Cook] Don't touch the cake!
- Get the tarts!

1170
01:19:12.620 --> 01:19:15.054
- Not me good ones!
- [Lily] Ow. he hit me!

1171
01:19:16.100 --> 01:19:18.011
- [Lily] Attack!
- Aaargh!

1172
01:19:19.740 --> 01:19:21.970
Not the cake! Not the cake!

1173
01:19:23.820 --> 01:19:26.459
Right! I'll have the lot of you!

1174
01:19:26.660 --> 01:19:29.220
Simon. bowling practice.

1175
01:19:34.620 --> 01:19:38.169
- [gasps]
- [whooping and shouting]

1176
01:19:58.300 --> 01:20:00.768
Evangeline. where are your manners?

1177
01:20:00.980 --> 01:20:02.698
Sod my manners. you old trout.

1178
01:20:02.900 --> 01:20:05.858
This is the first fun I've had in weeks!

1179
01:20:06.060 --> 01:20:10.576
- Oh. Lord.
- Letty. my hair. Where is it?

1180
01:20:10.780 --> 01:20:14.693
[as Mrs Quickly]
"Look at them. the little. small things."

1181
01:20:14.900 --> 01:20:19.928
That's it! You dreadful. awful.
monstrous creatures!

1182
01:20:20.140 --> 01:20:22.290
Take your hands off my children!

1183
01:20:22.500 --> 01:20:26.652
Cedric. it's over! I won't spend
another minute with this rabble

1184
01:20:26.860 --> 01:20:30.011
and I don't care how much
the old hag is giving you.

1185
01:20:30.220 --> 01:20:32.734
Letty. the lambs!

1186
01:20:33.580 --> 01:20:36.299
- [lambs bleat]
- [Letty whimpers]

1187
01:20:36.500 --> 01:20:39.219
- This dress is ruined!
- Absolute carnage!

1188
01:20:39.420 --> 01:20:43.049
A nice choice for a wife. I must say. Cedric.

1189
01:20:43.260 --> 01:20:46.013
I'm sorry. You gave me no time
to find anyone else.

1190
01:20:46.220 --> 01:20:51.453
As for your children. a lengthy spell
in a corrective institution is long overdue.

1191
01:20:51.660 --> 01:20:57.132
And you. Evangeline. I can see
that you are as wild as the rest of them.

1192
01:20:57.340 --> 01:21:01.379
And proud to be. I love them. Lady Stitch.
which is more than you do.

1193
01:21:01.580 --> 01:21:03.377
Insolence!

1194
01:21:03.580 --> 01:21:08.256
I'd leave you here to rot.
but I gave my word that I would raise you

1195
01:21:08.460 --> 01:21:12.294
and I never. ever. break my word.
Come away now.

1196
01:21:30.100 --> 01:21:32.933
[magical tinkling]

1197
01:21:37.300 --> 01:21:39.052
Wait. Aunt Adelaide! Wait!

1198
01:21:40.380 --> 01:21:42.575
You agreed. You gave your word

1199
01:21:42.780 --> 01:21:45.453
that if our father remarried this month.
you'd support us.

1200
01:21:45.660 --> 01:21:47.252
I did.

1201
01:21:47.460 --> 01:21:50.497
So if he marries today.
you'll have to keep your word.

1202
01:21:50.700 --> 01:21:53.134
- Oh. you're wasting my time!
- No.

1203
01:21:53.340 --> 01:21:56.059
No. No. I'm not.

1204
01:21:57.380 --> 01:21:59.336
- He will marry today.
- What?

1205
01:21:59.540 --> 01:22:00.609
- What?
- What?

1206
01:22:00.820 --> 01:22:01.775
What?

1207
01:22:01.980 --> 01:22:06.337
- Who?
- He'll marry Evangeline.

1208
01:22:14.980 --> 01:22:17.335
Incest?

1209
01:22:17.540 --> 01:22:21.328
No! No. Aunt Adelaide.
Evangeline isn't our sister.

1210
01:22:21.540 --> 01:22:23.974
- Not your sister?
- Of course she's not our sister.

1211
01:22:25.380 --> 01:22:27.416
Well. who is she. then?

1212
01:22:30.780 --> 01:22:33.135
I'm his scullery maid.

1213
01:22:33.340 --> 01:22:34.489
What?

1214
01:22:34.700 --> 01:22:37.897
Evangeline. do you love Papa?

1215
01:22:40.300 --> 01:22:44.612
Of course not. I know my place.
That wouldn't be right. I mean...

1216
01:22:46.460 --> 01:22:47.893
Yes.

1217
01:22:54.340 --> 01:22:56.251
Papa. do you love Evangeline?

1218
01:22:56.460 --> 01:22:58.576
What? That would be totally improper.

1219
01:22:58.780 --> 01:23:03.137
A thing like that could...could never happen.
I mean. obviously...

1220
01:23:08.700 --> 01:23:10.338
Yes.

1221
01:23:13.860 --> 01:23:17.216
He's marrying the scullery maid?

1222
01:23:17.420 --> 01:23:18.648
Oh!

1223
01:23:18.940 --> 01:23:21.977
- [thump]
- [magical tinkling]

1224
01:23:22.180 --> 01:23:23.499
[creaking]

1225
01:23:23.700 --> 01:23:27.090
- [crashing thud]
- [magical wind zings and whistles]

1226
01:24:06.820 --> 01:24:08.856
[child] It's snowing!

1227
01:24:09.060 --> 01:24:11.699
Well. I never! Snow!

1228
01:24:11.900 --> 01:24:14.255
Snow in August!

1229
01:24:34.420 --> 01:24:36.934
- [children laugh]
- I take it. then. Mr Brown.

1230
01:24:37.140 --> 01:24:40.576
that the young lady
is not in fact the fruit of your loins?

1231
01:24:40.780 --> 01:24:45.979
Because the Church would have to take
a rather dim view of it if she were.

1232
01:24:46.180 --> 01:24:50.173
No. What happened was my son Simon
is a very clever boy.

1233
01:24:50.380 --> 01:24:51.859
Evangeline...

1234
01:24:52.060 --> 01:24:55.211
for the record.
whatever I may have said about stepmothers.

1235
01:24:55.420 --> 01:24:57.297
that whole "evil breed" moment.

1236
01:24:57.500 --> 01:25:00.936
most emphatically does not apply to you.

1237
01:25:05.380 --> 01:25:07.416
This way.

1238
01:25:07.620 --> 01:25:13.331
Jolly good. If I may then invite you all
to join us once more.

1239
01:25:13.540 --> 01:25:14.973
Hallelujah.

1240
01:25:15.180 --> 01:25:19.537
Oh. Nanny McPhee... I'm so nervous.

1241
01:25:19.740 --> 01:25:21.776
Deep breaths.

1242
01:25:22.900 --> 01:25:25.858
I don't look much like a bride. do l?

1243
01:25:27.460 --> 01:25:29.576
You will.

1244
01:25:29.780 --> 01:25:33.659
[magical breeze fizzes and tinkles]

1245
01:26:19.860 --> 01:26:22.169
How's the reading coming along?

1246
01:26:22.380 --> 01:26:24.575
It's much better.

1247
01:26:24.780 --> 01:26:27.738
But I still haven't got to the end
of that story.

1248
01:26:27.940 --> 01:26:32.456
No need. You are the end of the story.

1249
01:26:52.260 --> 01:26:54.376
[parps nose mightily]

1250
01:26:58.300 --> 01:27:02.054
Dearly beloved. we are gathered together

1251
01:27:02.260 --> 01:27:05.969
to join together this man and this woman

1252
01:27:06.180 --> 01:27:09.252
in holy matrimony.

1253
01:27:14.740 --> 01:27:17.459
Make a loud noise and rejoice

1254
01:27:17.660 --> 01:27:19.776
and sing praise.

1255
01:27:22.020 --> 01:27:25.854
- [tinkling of bells]
- [rushing]

1256
01:27:35.500 --> 01:27:39.493
[Nanny McPhee] There is something
you should understand about the way I work.

1257
01:27:39.700 --> 01:27:44.535
When you need me but do not want me.
then I must stay.

1258
01:27:44.740 --> 01:27:48.494
When you want me but no longer need me.

1259
01:27:48.700 --> 01:27:50.736
then I have to go.

1260
01:28:05.220 --> 01:28:07.859
[magical tinkling]

1261
01:28:08.060 --> 01:28:10.369
- [creaking]
- [mighty thud]

1262
01:28:16.900 --> 01:28:19.698
[rubbery squeaking]

1263
01:28:23.860 --> 01:28:25.578
[boing!]

1264
01:28:34.300 --> 01:28:36.860
[squeaking]

1265
01:28:38.300 --> 01:28:39.892
[boing!]

1266
01:28:40.100 --> 01:28:42.330
[bubbling]

1267
01:28:45.860 --> 01:28:47.293
[boing!]

1268
01:28:55.180 --> 01:28:56.533
[creaking]

1269
01:28:56.740 --> 01:28:57.855
[mighty thud]

1270
01:28:58.060 --> 01:29:01.609
[rubbery squeaks and stretching]

1271
01:29:03.620 --> 01:29:05.815
[sloppy splotching]

1272
01:29:08.020 --> 01:29:10.659
[boing!]

1273
01:29:16.500 --> 01:29:18.968
- [rubbery stretching]
- [squelch]

1274
01:29:21.460 --> 01:29:24.020
[gloopy bubbling]

1275
01:29:26.220 --> 01:29:28.017
[boing!]

1276
01:29:38.260 --> 01:29:40.137
[boings]

1277
01:29:47.300 --> 01:29:49.530
[buzzing]

1278
01:29:50.580 --> 01:29:52.252
[croaks]

1279
01:29:55.540 --> 01:29:56.973
[croaks]

1280
01:30:05.020 --> 01:30:07.215
[rubbery stretching]

1281
01:30:12.300 --> 01:30:14.097
Yoo-hoo!

1282
01:30:17.980 --> 01:30:20.540
[magical tinkling]

1283
01:30:22.260 --> 01:30:24.171
- [creaking]
- [mighty thud]

1284
01:30:24.380 --> 01:30:27.531
[breeze sighs and fades away]

1285
01:34:19.380 --> 01:34:20.449
[creaking]

1286
01:34:20.660 --> 01:34:24.699
- [crashing thud]
- [magical breeze sighs]
